0
00:00:15,133 --> 00:00:16,727
马普尔小姐探案
制作 Lyra

1
00:00:35,663 --> 00:00:38,604
1932年,烟囱大厦,晚宴

2
00:00:52,668 --> 00:00:55,385
不,不,不,别去,别去
No, no, no. Please, please.

3
00:00:55,385 --> 00:00:58,620
不,不.您不能往那边去,求您
No, no. You mustn't go in there, please, sir.

4
00:00:58,620 --> 00:01:00,109
求您听我的
Now, listen to what I'm saying.

5
00:01:02,330 --> 00:01:04,784
求您听我的,求您别过去
Please listen to me. No, please, please.

6
00:01:08,002 --> 00:01:11,880
名苑猎凶

7
00:01:12,185 --> 00:01:13,435
伦敦 蓓尔美尔街俱乐部 23年后

8
00:01:13,655 --> 00:01:16,572
凯特勒姆,老伙计,我不该问
Caterham, my dear chap, I wouldn't ask,

9
00:01:16,572 --> 00:01:20,328
只不过此事关系重大
only it's a matter of considerable national importance.

10
00:01:20,328 --> 00:01:21,951
总是事关重大不是吗?
Isn't it always?

11
00:01:21,951 --> 00:01:24,809
维也纳那边有了很大进展
We've had the most tremendous approach from Vienna.

12
00:01:24,809 --> 00:01:25,619
继续说
Go on.

13
00:01:25,619 --> 00:01:28,038
奥地利现在成了中立国
Now the Austrians are a nice neutral bunch,

14
00:01:28,038 --> 00:01:30,031
他们很急切地想跟我们英国成为朋友
they're very keen to be friends with us Brits.

15
00:01:30,031 --> 00:01:31,315
什么条件?
What's the offer?

16
00:01:31,315 --> 00:01:33,451
铁矿石
Iron ore.

17
00:01:33,451 --> 00:01:36,859
我们去帮助他们的重工业重整旗鼓
We go in, help them put their heavy industry back on its feet,

18
00:01:36,859 --> 00:01:38,784
可以要多少铁矿拿多少
take home all the iron ore we need.

19
00:01:38,784 --> 00:01:41,050
首相简直不敢相信会有这么好的买卖
The PM can scarcely believe his luck.

20
00:01:41,050 --> 00:01:42,995
不管怎样,维也纳方面要派来一位公使
Anyway, Vienna's sending over an envoy.

21
00:01:42,995 --> 00:01:44,704
路德维格伯爵
Count Ludwig.

22
00:01:44,704 --> 00:01:48,472
我分到的任务是为伯爵安排住处,并且开始起草合约
I've been tasked with sitting the Count down, putting pen to paper

23
00:01:48,472 --> 00:01:50,508
然后设法让他签字
and getting him to sign the contract.

24
00:01:50,508 --> 00:01:53,328
得找个红花绿草,心旷神怡,最重要的是能谈事的地方
Somewhere green and pleasant and, above all, discreet.

25
00:01:53,784 --> 00:01:56,010
你想让他住烟囱大厦?
And you thought of Chimneys?

26
00:01:56,010 --> 00:01:58,386
嗯,你懂的,周末开个室内宴会
Well, you know, a weekend house party.

27
00:01:58,386 --> 00:02:00,866
好酒好菜
Good food, decent cellar.

28
00:02:00,866 --> 00:02:04,029
像以前那样,诶?你说怎么样?行吗?
Just like the old days, eh? What do you say? Do the ayes have it?

29
00:02:04,029 --> 00:02:07,404
实际上,我下个月还想出去度假呢
Well, actually, I was thinking of going on holiday next month.

30
00:02:07,404 --> 00:02:10,143
别瞎扯了,谁9月份出去度假啊
Oh, nonsense. Nobody goes on holiday in September.

31
00:02:10,143 --> 00:02:13,157
再说,咱俩谁跟谁啊
Besides, we're practically family you and I.

32
00:02:13,157 --> 00:02:16,393
只等着你家女儿想通了
Once we bring that girl of yours to her senses.

33
00:02:18,582 --> 00:02:21,893
我们家不如从前啦,房子有点失修
We're not as we were. The house is in some disrepair.

34
00:02:21,893 --> 00:02:25,635
很好啊,有点沧桑感,增加几分情趣
Perfect. Faded grandeur. Adds to the flavour.

35
00:02:26,233 --> 00:02:27,974
这事不能张扬出去
It'll need to be low-key.

36
00:02:27,974 --> 00:02:31,448
那是自然的,只叫好朋友来,此事要谨慎处理
Indeed so. Intimate. Discreet.

37
00:02:31,448 --> 00:02:34,402
选一两个"合适"的客人
One or two guests, sensitively chosen.

38
00:02:34,835 --> 00:02:37,736
当然了,这些个欧洲人都是些势利眼
Of course, these continentals are such fearful snobs.

39
00:02:38,514 --> 00:02:41,017
我会叫我最得力的手下去帮忙的
I'll send my best chap round to help with the setting up.

40
00:02:41,017 --> 00:02:43,445
比尔埃弗斯利,听候差遣
Bill Eversleigh. Yours to serve.

41
00:02:44,125 --> 00:02:45,355
你好
How do you do?

42
00:02:47,275 --> 00:02:50,936
为什么选择烟囱大厦?我们都很多年没举办宴会了
But why Chimneys? It's years since we gave a party.

43
00:02:50,936 --> 00:02:53,752
几十年了,32年以后就没举办过
Decades. Not since '32.

44
00:02:54,106 --> 00:02:55,349
给他看看那封信
Show him the letter.

45
00:02:55,976 --> 00:02:58,285
哪封?   路德维格伯爵写的
The...?   From Count Ludwig.

46
00:03:04,489 --> 00:03:05,886
你看
Here we are.

47
00:03:07,007 --> 00:03:08,361
第四段
Fourth para.

48
00:03:08,610 --> 00:03:10,306
从中间开始读
Halfway down.

49
00:03:10,306 --> 00:03:14,298
我久仰烟囱大厦的大名,听说是英国老建筑里
I have heard that Chimneys is the most prized house...

50
00:03:14,298 --> 00:03:15,884
最负盛名的
 ..in old England,

51
00:03:15,884 --> 00:03:18,376
如果能瞻仰这座美丽的宫殿
and would count it a singular honour

52
00:03:18,376 --> 00:03:22,104
将是鄙人的无上荣幸
to see that jewelled palace for myself.

53
00:03:22,510 --> 00:03:26,587
这将成为我最想要珍藏的记忆
It is a memory I am most eager to cherish.

54
00:03:43,891 --> 00:03:45,966
要是我吓着你了很抱歉
Sorry to drop in unannounced.

55
00:03:45,966 --> 00:03:48,754
你要是合作我也会温柔一些
If you're gentle with me then I'll be gentle with you.

56
00:03:48,754 --> 00:03:50,460
啊!
Agh!

57
00:03:54,254 --> 00:03:55,478
救命!
Help!

58
00:04:13,506 --> 00:04:15,278
永远,不要...
Never, ever...

59
00:04:16,865 --> 00:04:19,095
碰我妈妈的自行车
..touch mother's bicycle again.

60
00:04:20,793 --> 00:04:23,127
你没事吧?能站起来吗?
Are you all right? Can you stand?

61
00:04:23,127 --> 00:04:25,309
哦,是的,我...   这是最主要的
Oh, yes, I...   Well, that's the main thing.

62
00:04:25,309 --> 00:04:27,469
只要能站起来,一切就...
Once you're up on your pins, then life seems so...

63
00:04:30,366 --> 00:04:32,154
皆有可能
Full of possibility.

64
00:04:33,630 --> 00:04:34,893
没错
Indeed.

65
00:04:36,921 --> 00:04:38,829
我倒不是只在乎我妈的自行车,你知道
Not that I was purely concerned about 

66
00:04:38,829 --> 00:04:40,774
我倒不是只在乎我妈的自行车,你知道
poor mother's bicycle, you understand.

67
00:04:41,917 --> 00:04:43,579
我希望不是
Well, I should hope not.

68
00:04:44,355 --> 00:04:46,984
我想那家伙应该吸取教训了,你说呢?
I think the chap got the message, don't you?

69
00:04:52,081 --> 00:04:55,036
他就这么铁马王子一般地冲出来救了我
And there he was, galloping in to save me on his iron horse.

70
00:04:55,036 --> 00:04:58,043
真是世界上最二的骑士了
I mean it really was the most idiotically chivalrous...

71
00:04:58,043 --> 00:04:59,273
怎么了?
What?

72
00:05:00,044 --> 00:05:01,112
弗吉尼亚
Virginia.

73
00:05:01,112 --> 00:05:04,451
你和你亲爱的妈妈一样是无可救药的浪漫主义者
You are as absurdly romantic as your dear mother.

74
00:05:04,451 --> 00:05:05,569
哦,太没有呢
Oh, no. No, no, no.

75
00:05:05,569 --> 00:05:08,000
你这话可说的不对.你要是真的觉得...
Woof woof. Wrong tree. If you honestly...

76
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,134
他是最不合适的人了
He couldn't be more unsuitable.

77
00:05:10,134 --> 00:05:11,581
没钱没钱途
No cash, no prospects.

78
00:05:11,581 --> 00:05:14,967
哦,如果是这样的话...   是啊,就是这样了
Oh, well, then.   Yes, quite. Case closed.

79
00:05:15,794 --> 00:05:18,753
再者说了,他这周对我很冷淡
And, anyway, he's been quite standoffish with me this past week.

80
00:05:19,734 --> 00:05:21,970
大概是觉得无聊了,你说呢?
I expect he's bored of me. Don't you?

81
00:05:21,970 --> 00:05:24,177
哦,必须的.他叫什么?
Oh, yes. Does he have a name?

82
00:05:24,484 --> 00:05:28,976
安东尼凯德"阁下".不过是打引号的
Sir Anthony Cade. Only without the knighthood.

83
00:05:38,704 --> 00:05:41,896
哦,天啊,我还想呢
Oh, dear. I was just thinking.

84
00:05:41,896 --> 00:05:43,873
你那位可怜的国会议员
Your poor MP.

85
00:05:44,881 --> 00:05:47,844
乔治洛马克斯可一刻不耽误
George Lomax won't be the least bit put off.

86
00:05:47,931 --> 00:05:49,228
恰恰相反
On the contrary.

87
00:05:49,228 --> 00:05:51,117
又给你下最后通牒了?
Not another ultimatum?

88
00:05:51,117 --> 00:05:54,363
我要在周日晚上前答应做他太太
I have until Sunday night to consent to be Mrs George Lomax.

89
00:05:54,363 --> 00:05:57,242
要不然呢?   他大概就要入侵波兰了
Or what?   He invades Poland, I suppose.

90
00:05:58,401 --> 00:06:00,394
不管怎么说,他开的条件还是很好的
Anyway, the terms are most generous.

91
00:06:00,786 --> 00:06:03,001
他会安排爸爸在镇上的豪宅住下
He'll put daddy up in a mansion flat in town,

92
00:06:03,001 --> 00:06:05,424
这正合他心意,自从妈妈死了之后他一直想这样
which is all he wants since Mama passed away.

93
00:06:05,424 --> 00:06:08,014
他还会出钱维持烟囱大厦
And he'll even pay to stop Chimneys from falling apart,

94
00:06:08,014 --> 00:06:11,061
我想这对家族很好
which I suppose is jolly good for the family.

95
00:06:11,061 --> 00:06:12,494
前提是你嫁给他
If you marry him.

96
00:06:13,477 --> 00:06:15,714
显然大家期望我会心怀感激
I should be more grateful, obviously.

97
00:06:16,344 --> 00:06:21,474
我想感激大概不是一段幸福婚姻的基石
Well, I'm not sure gratitude is the basis for a happy marriage.

98
00:06:22,181 --> 00:06:25,370
不过话说回来,这方面我没什么发言资格
Well, no, no. Not that I am any sort of expert.

99
00:06:25,370 --> 00:06:26,994
哪的话,妈妈一直说你是她所有亲戚里最理智的了
No, no, no, no, Mummy always said

100
00:06:26,994 --> 00:06:29,583
哪的话,妈妈一直说你是她所有亲戚里最理智的了
 you were the most eminently sensible of all her cousins.

101
00:06:30,873 --> 00:06:34,309
她的婚姻是非常成功的
Well, she certainly made a splendid marriage.

102
00:06:34,309 --> 00:06:37,850
要说幸福啊,本该很简单的不是吗?
It should be so simple, shouldn't it, being happy?

103
00:06:37,850 --> 00:06:40,710
应该是一见倾心的,不是吗
I mean, one ought to see it, and just know.

104
00:06:41,956 --> 00:06:44,424
现在你来了,我们要放纵一下
Well, now that I've got you here 

105
00:06:44,424 --> 00:06:46,773
现在你来了,我们要放纵一下
we are going to have a riot, you and I.

106
00:06:46,773 --> 00:06:49,708
这是我待字闺中的最后一个周末了
My last weekend as an eligible spinster.

107
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:52,756
你玩游戏吗?   我尽量吧
Are you game?   Well, I'll do my best.

108
00:06:55,269 --> 00:06:56,460
好了!
Well!

109
00:06:58,608 --> 00:07:02,494
我来这里住你父亲没意见吗?
Are you quite sure it's all right with your father, having me along?

110
00:07:02,494 --> 00:07:04,525
爸爸很高兴呢
Oh, Daddy's thrilled.

111
00:07:04,525 --> 00:07:06,826
再说我也去圣玛丽米德做过客
And, anyway, you've had me down to St Mary Mead.

112
00:07:06,826 --> 00:07:08,962
礼尚往来嘛
It's only fair I return the favour.

113
00:07:08,962 --> 00:07:11,830
来,看.17页
Here, look. Page 17.

114
00:07:12,297 --> 00:07:13,794
是不是个帅锅?
Isn't he a dish?

115
00:07:17,345 --> 00:07:19,092
安东尼凯德
Anthony Cade.

116
00:07:19,984 --> 00:07:21,534
一时兴起罢了
Some passing whim.

117
00:07:23,235 --> 00:07:26,422
弗吉尼亚很纯真,很容易受触动.这也是她的魅力
Virginia is innocent, easily led. It's all part of her charm.

118
00:07:26,422 --> 00:07:28,167
也许她只是玩玩罢了
Perhaps she's off for a bit of fun, sir.

119
00:07:28,353 --> 00:07:31,816
我的好伙伴
My short trousers chum,

120
00:07:31,816 --> 00:07:34,683
我们总得学会放下这些幼稚的东西
We must all learn to put away, childish things.

121
00:07:35,590 --> 00:07:37,594
她不是把凯德也叫来了吧
I say she's not bringing Cade along, is she?

122
00:07:37,594 --> 00:07:39,493
没有,先生.她带了一位马普尔小姐来
No, sir. She's coming with a Miss Marple.

123
00:07:39,493 --> 00:07:40,384
我们认识这人吗?
Do we know her?

124
00:07:40,712 --> 00:07:41,807
我想不认识
Not that I'm aware of.

125
00:07:41,807 --> 00:07:43,766
我以为你核对过客人的名单了
I thought you were cross the guest list.

126
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:47,098
我核对过了,当然核对过了
Oh, I am, absolutely.

127
00:07:47,098 --> 00:07:50,979
马普尔小姐,一听就是没见过世面的小姑娘
Marple, some fresh hatch little...

128
00:07:51,669 --> 00:07:53,023
跟你很搭呢
Something for you obviously.

129
00:07:55,454 --> 00:08:01,343
至于弗吉尼亚,我希望你对她没什么念头
Regarding Virginia, I trust you have no ambition of your own.

130
00:08:01,928 --> 00:08:04,272
哪会呀   因为你是没希望的
What's a question?   Because that wouldn't do at all.

131
00:08:06,161 --> 00:08:08,210
我不想你受伤而已
One wouldn't want you to be hurt.

132
00:08:08,263 --> 00:08:10,644
受伤的机会都没有,先生
No chance of that, sir.

133
00:08:17,280 --> 00:08:18,311
什么事,柴德维尔?
Yes, Treadwell?

134
00:08:18,311 --> 00:08:20,002
你的客人到了,先生
Your guest has arrived, sir.

135
00:08:20,314 --> 00:08:21,175
这么快?
Already?

136
00:08:21,803 --> 00:08:26,039
肩往后,关键时刻到了,学着点
Shoulders back. Cometh the hour. Watch and learn.

137
00:08:26,887 --> 00:08:28,983
爵爷桌上的信
Letters for posting on his Lordship's table.

138
00:08:28,983 --> 00:08:31,323
请您用快递寄出去
Send them express, if you'd be so kind.

139
00:08:34,881 --> 00:08:36,095
路德维格伯爵,您好!
Count Ludwig!

140
00:08:41,543 --> 00:08:42,910
瞧瞧
Oh, look.

141
00:08:42,910 --> 00:08:45,042
他要亲上人家的屁股了
He's practically licking his shoes.

142
00:08:45,042 --> 00:08:48,343
伯爵要以为这是英国的奇风异俗了
The Count might think it's some sort of quaint British custom.

143
00:08:53,822 --> 00:09:00,232
您的到来是我国的荣幸

144
00:09:00,790 --> 00:09:03,505
有点早了,这样更好
A little early, but so much the better.

145
00:09:03,505 --> 00:09:06,704
恰恰相反,我来的太晚了

146
00:09:09,247 --> 00:09:11,758
是啊,这房子很美
Indeed, a lovely house, yes.

147
00:09:11,758 --> 00:09:13,736
他像是上个世纪的人似的
He seems like he's from another age.

148
00:09:14,141 --> 00:09:16,057
你说他能不能说英语啊
I wonder if he speaks any English.

149
00:09:16,057 --> 00:09:18,783
签张支票需要会几句英语呀?
How much English do you need to sign a cheque?

150
00:09:18,783 --> 00:09:22,404
我...金属...你...钞票大大地
Me metal. You big, big dollars.

151
00:09:28,042 --> 00:09:29,457
玛德琳?
Madeleine?

152
00:09:31,410 --> 00:09:33,787
爸爸,别傻了,我是弗吉尼亚啊
Don't embarress yourself, papa, it's Virginia.

153
00:09:34,528 --> 00:09:37,991
是弗吉尼亚啊,我来看看你
Virginia. Pops in a visit.

154
00:09:37,991 --> 00:09:40,538
是啊,我没听到你进来
Yes, I didn't hear you come in.

155
00:09:40,661 --> 00:09:41,634
爸爸您好!
Hello Daddy!

156
00:09:42,699 --> 00:09:44,052
真抱歉,亲爱的
So sorry, darling.

157
00:09:44,842 --> 00:09:47,019
啊,亲爱的简
Ah, dear Jane.

158
00:09:47,230 --> 00:09:48,293
克莱门特
Clement.

159
00:09:48,782 --> 00:09:51,973
都有...多少年...   是啊,自从葬礼就没见了   是啊
It's been... Well...   Yes, not since the funeral.   Yes.

160
00:09:52,770 --> 00:09:56,983
玛德琳死后你一直对我女儿这么好   惭愧
You've been so kind to my daughter since we lost Madeleine.   No.

161
00:09:56,983 --> 00:09:57,995
你的花园怎么样了
How's your garden?

162
00:09:58,634 --> 00:10:00,966
不怎么繁茂啊
Hardly thriving, I'm afraid.

163
00:10:00,966 --> 00:10:04,255
爸爸,你也整理一下自己的仪容啊
Daddy, you might have made a bit of an effort.

164
00:10:04,255 --> 00:10:07,601
不用管我,我现在就是个怪老头了
Oh, pay no attention to me. I'm just the odd-job man these days.

165
00:10:07,601 --> 00:10:11,927
哦,看啊,这不是那位国家遗产局的那个女人吗
Oh, look. I see you've invited that nice lady from National Heritage.

166
00:10:12,845 --> 00:10:14,649
希尔达贝金索普?
Hilda Blenkinsopp?

167
00:10:15,513 --> 00:10:19,305
不,不. 哦,不!
No. No. Oh, no!

168
00:10:19,357 --> 00:10:23,376
班铎,别生气,她很想来这里
Now, Bundle, don't get cross. She was very keen to be invited...

169
00:10:23,376 --> 00:10:24,846
我们说好不让她再来了
She's banned. We agreed.

170
00:10:24,846 --> 00:10:28,628
对,但是国家遗产局出价很合适
Yes, but the National Heritage have made a very sensible offer.

171
00:10:28,628 --> 00:10:31,804
烟囱大厦已经在这个家族传了几代人了,它就是这个家的一部分
Chimneys has been in the family for centuries. It is family.

172
00:10:31,804 --> 00:10:35,024
没错亲爱的,但是我们已经负担不起了,这你知道的
Yes, but, darling, you know we can't afford to keep the place on.

173
00:10:35,434 --> 00:10:38,491
我们会想办法的,我们总是能想到办法
We will manage. We always do.

174
00:10:40,918 --> 00:10:43,269
她心情不错啊
Well, she's on good form.

175
00:10:44,996 --> 00:10:50,768
国家遗产局已经接手郡里13座老宅子了
National Heritage has taken on 13 homes and gardens in the county.

176
00:10:52,642 --> 00:10:55,961
为贵族而建,为人民而维系
Built for the few, fit for the many, 

177
00:10:55,961 --> 00:10:58,203
我就是冲着这样的前景努力的   谢谢
that's the England I'm fighting for.   Thank you.

178
00:10:58,203 --> 00:11:00,155
巫婆的计谋得逞了
The witch found who she want.

179
00:11:02,126 --> 00:11:06,438
不管怎么说,你都想不到人们是怎么涌入这些个老房子的
Still, you'd be amazed how these old places fill up.

180
00:11:06,438 --> 00:11:09,805
有钱人的旧宅,谁不想看看啊
Homes of the former great, draw such a crowd.

181
00:11:09,805 --> 00:11:11,278
特别是到了周末
Especially at the weekends.

182
00:11:12,349 --> 00:11:14,263
等我们把那块土地清理好
Once we get that patch sorted out.

183
00:11:14,263 --> 00:11:18,787
那块土地!这些花园是国王设计的
That patch! These gardens were designed by King.

184
00:11:18,787 --> 00:11:22,245
是嘛,谁都有闲得没事的时候啊
Oh, well, dear, I suppose we all have our off days.

185
00:11:22,666 --> 00:11:25,234
上流社会啊,埃弗斯利.我说什么来着!
High society, Eversleigh. What did I say?

186
00:11:25,234 --> 00:11:26,555
提升环境的品味,先生
Embellish the scene, sir. 

187
00:11:26,555 --> 00:11:30,043
提升环境的品味,科学家,工业巨头...
Embellish the scene. Scientists. Captains of industry...

188
00:11:30,043 --> 00:11:32,965
你都带了谁?拖把头和水桶腰
What do you bring me? Mrs Mop and Mrs Bucket.

189
00:11:32,965 --> 00:11:35,013
特勒姆说灌点杜松子酒
Caterham says they're both first class 

190
00:11:35,013 --> 00:11:36,509
两位就都是上流社会的人了
if you get a bit of gin down them.

191
00:11:36,509 --> 00:11:38,564
哦,是嘛?   有问题吗?
Oh, does he?   Problem?

192
00:11:38,852 --> 00:11:40,224
完全没有,先生
Not at all, sir.

193
00:11:40,680 --> 00:11:43,628
您的客人很...多元化
Very diverse guest list.

194
00:11:43,628 --> 00:11:46,001
很好,那我要去跟她们聊聊了
Good. Well, I should join in.

195
00:11:49,417 --> 00:11:50,944
你特意安排的吗?
Was this your doing?

196
00:11:52,801 --> 00:11:55,254
乔治要接受我们真实的样子
George will have to take us as he finds us.

197
00:11:57,225 --> 00:11:59,788
怎么了?   嫁给我吧
What?   Marry me.

198
00:12:00,709 --> 00:12:02,537
比尔
Bill.

199
00:12:04,032 --> 00:12:06,679
女人空腹的时候可别求婚
Never propose on an empty stomach.

200
00:12:06,679 --> 00:12:08,691
晚饭之后再问我吧
Ask me again after supper.

201
00:12:08,691 --> 00:12:10,732
你没事情要做吗?
Don't you have to be somewhere?

202
00:12:23,520 --> 00:12:25,656
挺热的是不是?
Sultry, isn't it?

203
00:12:27,549 --> 00:12:29,195
你做头发了吗?
What have you done to your hair?

204
00:12:29,195 --> 00:12:31,151
没有
Not a thing.

205
00:12:31,151 --> 00:12:33,628
你能注意到真好啊,亲爱的
Sweet of you to notice, darling.

206
00:12:33,628 --> 00:12:37,679
你没忘记你答应会在周日晚上前回复我吧?
You haven't forgotten that you promised me an answer by Sunday night?

207
00:12:38,431 --> 00:12:39,773
就快要到了
The clock is ticking.

208
00:12:47,776 --> 00:12:52,262
请原谅,但是你们看起来太美了
Forgive me, but you all looked so perfect.

209
00:12:52,262 --> 00:12:55,146
像是画里出来的人
Like you had stepped out of a photograph.

210
00:12:55,146 --> 00:12:58,448
路德维格伯爵,请允许我介绍,克莱门特瑞佛
Count Ludwig, allow me to introduce Clement Revel,

211
00:12:58,448 --> 00:13:00,440
凯特勒姆家族的第九代
Ninth Marquis of Caterham.

212
00:13:00,904 --> 00:13:03,670
您好   很高兴认识您
How do you do?   The honour is entirely mine.

213
00:13:03,670 --> 00:13:05,451
晚上好,夫人们
Good evening, madam.

214
00:13:06,420 --> 00:13:10,118
这两位就是您女儿吗?
And these are your two little Revels?

215
00:13:10,736 --> 00:13:13,127
能赏脸吗?
Would you indulge a fading guest?

216
00:13:13,884 --> 00:13:15,044
赏个光嘛
Why not?

217
00:13:15,044 --> 00:13:18,784
我真的不会跳舞.您邀请她跳吧
I've two left feet. So why don't you try her?

218
00:13:18,784 --> 00:13:20,538
反正大家都喜欢她
Because everyone else seems to.

219
00:13:31,154 --> 00:13:32,856
节奏感多好啊
Oh, for a sense of rhythm.

220
00:13:33,208 --> 00:13:35,534
舞姿真优雅
Such a graceful dancer.

221
00:13:35,534 --> 00:13:37,594
他们都跳的不错不是吗?
Well, they all are, aren't they?

222
00:13:37,594 --> 00:13:41,714
不过这可算不上是什么有实用的修养
Still, hardly the most practical accomplishment.

223
00:13:41,714 --> 00:13:43,892
您第一次来英国吗?
Is this your first visit to our shores?

224
00:13:43,892 --> 00:13:47,276
不,我都来过好几次了
No, I am an inveterate itinerant, I'm afraid.

225
00:13:47,276 --> 00:13:50,706
至少年轻的时候常来
Or I was, once upon a time.

226
00:13:50,728 --> 00:13:53,205
您在笑话我呢
Now you are laughing at me.

227
00:13:53,205 --> 00:13:55,211
没有,没有,只是您的英语
No, no, no, it's just your English.

228
00:13:55,211 --> 00:13:56,300
说得真好
Splendid.

229
00:13:56,300 --> 00:13:58,586
我的老师很严格的
I had a highly disciplined teacher, you see.

230
00:13:58,586 --> 00:14:01,341
她只教我说绕口令
She taught me only tongue-twisters.

231
00:14:02,731 --> 00:14:04,786
吃葡萄不吐葡萄皮
Inveterate itinerant.

232
00:14:04,786 --> 00:14:06,697
吃葡萄不吐葡萄皮
Inveterate itinerant.

233
00:14:06,697 --> 00:14:08,816
吃葡萄不吐葡萄皮
Inveterate itinerant!

234
00:14:10,615 --> 00:14:12,462
晚饭要凉了
Your dinner is getting cold.

235
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:15,268
很好,非常好
Very good. Excellent.

236
00:14:23,605 --> 00:14:27,130
班铎,你带大家进去啊?   好啊
Bundle, will you lead on?   Yes, of course.

237
00:14:27,130 --> 00:14:29,619
贝金索普小姐,您先请
Miss Blenkinsopp, after you.

238
00:14:29,619 --> 00:14:31,082
请跟我来,小姐们
Follow me, ladies.

239
00:14:41,241 --> 00:14:43,472
您能来真好
Very good, you're with us.

240
00:14:46,905 --> 00:14:48,798
您来吗?   哦
Shall we?   Oh.

241
00:15:08,902 --> 00:15:10,873
晚餐很不错,谢谢
A splendid dinner, thank you.

242
00:15:10,873 --> 00:15:12,104
是的,很丰盛
Yes, very filling.

243
00:15:12,104 --> 00:15:13,511
请允许我问一下
Forgive my asking, sir. 

244
00:15:13,511 --> 00:15:16,617
您想来我家是因为这建筑吗?
Your interest in my house, is it for architecture?

245
00:15:16,617 --> 00:15:20,663
不,不,我对建筑并不懂
No, no. I have no head for grand design, for architecture.

246
00:15:21,799 --> 00:15:24,887
你家的画...   好的大都卖掉了
Your paintings...   We sold most of the decent ones.

247
00:15:24,887 --> 00:15:26,696
我们还留着这副凡代克的画
We still have our Van Dyck.

248
00:15:26,696 --> 00:15:27,824
是啊
So I see.

249
00:15:28,656 --> 00:15:31,736
这位是什么人啊?   一位什么公爵的
Who is this fellow?   Some old duke.

250
00:15:32,372 --> 00:15:34,661
里士满的呢
Richmond. Duke of.

251
00:15:34,719 --> 00:15:37,027
里士满,是啊
Richmond. Yes.

252
00:15:37,027 --> 00:15:42,081
要是既不为了艺术品,也不为了建筑,那是...?
So if it's not the art, or the architecture, then...?

253
00:15:42,081 --> 00:15:44,067
历史啊
Oh, the history.

254
00:15:44,308 --> 00:15:47,364
据说这房子接待过不少伟大的人
The great men rumoured to have met within these walls.

255
00:15:47,364 --> 00:15:49,671
签订条约,探讨政务
Treaties, affairs of state,

256
00:15:49,671 --> 00:15:54,282
甚至战争也在这里的咖啡和雪茄间开始和结束
wars, even, begun and ended here over coffee and cigars.

257
00:15:54,282 --> 00:15:57,300
哪有这么玄乎呀
Oh, nothing so biblical, I assure you.

258
00:15:58,087 --> 00:16:00,086
凯特勒姆这是在谦虚呢
He's being modest, aren't you, Caterham?

259
00:16:00,438 --> 00:16:02,868
烟囱大厦名声在外
Chimneys had quite a reputation.

260
00:16:03,414 --> 00:16:05,361
那现在怎么沦落了?
So what happened?

261
00:16:05,456 --> 00:16:06,414
你说什么?
What was that?

262
00:16:06,805 --> 00:16:08,845
出了点事
We ran into some bother.

263
00:16:09,558 --> 00:16:12,653
你是说1932年的那次宴会?
Oh, the party of 1932?

264
00:16:12,653 --> 00:16:14,521
哦,老黄历了
Oh, that old yarn.

265
00:16:15,085 --> 00:16:18,673
我们刚从加拉加斯(委内瑞拉首都)回国来
Well, we'd come back from an embassy posting. Caracas.

266
00:16:18,673 --> 00:16:20,664
结果那也是我最后一次做驻外大使了
It was my last one, as it turned out.

267
00:16:20,664 --> 00:16:22,280
那年弗吉尼亚还没出生呢
It was before Virginia was born.

268
00:16:22,793 --> 00:16:24,387
不管怎样,那晚真是不错
Anyway, it was quite a night.

269
00:16:24,983 --> 00:16:27,211
你妈妈很会举办宴会的,花园里还有请来的乐队在演奏
Your mother always gave wonderful parties, 

270
00:16:27,211 --> 00:16:28,733
你妈妈很会举办宴会的,花园里还有请来的乐队在演奏
with a band out in the garden.

271
00:16:28,733 --> 00:16:30,343
我听说过
I remember the story, yes.

272
00:16:30,732 --> 00:16:32,459
你当时还在场呢,是不是乔治?
You were there yourself, weren't you, George?

273
00:16:32,482 --> 00:16:37,035
去帮把手.我陪着索梅塞夫人去的
Helping out. I was accompanying Lady Somerset.

274
00:16:37,035 --> 00:16:40,227
我很受...启发
It was um...most instructive.

275
00:16:41,894 --> 00:16:43,246
这张照片就是那时拍的吗?
Is this it here?

276
00:16:43,246 --> 00:16:46,430
是的.   这是在哪?
Yes.   Where is that?

277
00:16:46,430 --> 00:16:48,266
玫瑰园   啊
The rose garden.   Ah.

278
00:16:48,266 --> 00:16:50,456
我们动人的维也纳华尔兹
Our lovely Viennese waltz.

279
00:16:52,144 --> 00:16:54,372
您的歌声真好听   谢谢
Charming singing voice.   Thank you.

280
00:16:54,372 --> 00:16:56,189
不过,那晚还出了点事
Anyway, there was a bit of a to-do

281
00:16:56,189 --> 00:16:58,066
索梅塞公爵夫人当晚借来了一个很大的胸针戴着...
because the Duchess of Somerset

282
00:16:58,066 --> 00:17:01,613
索梅塞公爵夫人当晚借来了一个很大的胸针戴着...
had borrowed a large brooch for the evening. On her...

283
00:17:01,613 --> 00:17:02,704
大胸针?
Large brooch?

284
00:17:02,704 --> 00:17:05,720
爸爸,那是印度迈索尔的钻石
Daddy, it was the Mysore Diamond from India,

285
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:09,248
大概是世界上最有名的钻石了
possibly the most revered diamond in the world.

286
00:17:09,248 --> 00:17:13,571
嗯,不管是啥,早餐的时候发现它不见了
Well, whatever it was, by breakfast time it had disappeared.

287
00:17:13,571 --> 00:17:19,323
被偷了,被个一无是处的客厅女仆,叫艾格尼丝的偷走了
Stolen. By some good-for-nothing parlour maid named Agnes.

288
00:17:19,323 --> 00:17:22,762
客厅女仆,像小说里的故事呢!
A parlour maid. What an English saga!

289
00:17:22,762 --> 00:17:25,964
那个女仆当晚就失踪了,不是吗?
The maid vanished overnight. Isn't that right?

290
00:17:25,964 --> 00:17:29,030
钻石也再没找到
And the diamond was never ever to be found again.

291
00:17:29,030 --> 00:17:31,614
还要咖啡吗?   哦,是的,谢谢
Anyone for more coffee?   Oh, yes, please.

292
00:17:31,614 --> 00:17:36,833
这个艾格尼丝是个什么样的女孩子?
So what sort of girl was she, this Agnes?

293
00:17:37,671 --> 00:17:39,353
也许没人注意过她?
Or did nobody notice?

294
00:17:39,353 --> 00:17:43,309
只有19岁,我想肯定是一时冲昏了头脑
Well, only 19 years old. She must have lost her head, I suppose.

295
00:17:43,309 --> 00:17:48,850
不管怎样,这件事让我的外交生涯结束了
Anyway, it meant the end of my career in the diplomatic service.

296
00:17:50,714 --> 00:17:52,780
说起来真是丢人
All rather shameful.

297
00:17:55,512 --> 00:17:58,336
女士们能不能让我们单独...
Well, if the ladies can spare us...?

298
00:17:58,336 --> 00:18:01,148
谈生意   是,当然
To business.   Indeed. Yes.

299
00:18:01,148 --> 00:18:03,154
我给你们生意
I give you business.

300
00:18:03,154 --> 00:18:07,347
你要我们的铁矿啊,洛马克斯议员?
You want our iron, Mr Lomax, MP?

301
00:18:08,068 --> 00:18:12,090
那是当然的   我只提出一个要求
Well, naturally.   I make one request.

302
00:18:12,782 --> 00:18:14,186
烟囱大厦
Chimneys.

303
00:18:16,131 --> 00:18:19,021
把烟囱大厦作为给我个人的礼物
Give me Chimneys as a personal favour. And, in return, I guarantee

304
00:18:19,021 --> 00:18:21,105
作为回报,我会保证,你们能要多少拿多少
Give me Chimneys as a personal favour. And, in return, I guarantee

305
00:18:21,105 --> 00:18:25,215
作为回报,我会保证,你们能要多少拿多少
you can take home all the riches your heart desires.

306
00:18:25,215 --> 00:18:28,390
这我不知道...   我们不卖房子
Well, I'm not sure...   We are not for sale.

307
00:18:28,390 --> 00:18:31,123
不卖,你说啊
Not for sale. Tell them.

308
00:18:32,172 --> 00:18:35,573
你们去打打桥牌怎么样?
Why don't you all try a hand of bridge?

309
00:18:35,573 --> 00:18:37,293
哦,真见鬼   好的
Oh, for God's sake.   Yes.

310
00:18:52,868 --> 00:18:55,352
你确定了吗?    是的
You're quite sure?    Absolutely.

311
00:18:55,352 --> 00:18:59,090
那好,在这里...签字
Very well. Then mark your cross... ..here.

312
00:19:05,184 --> 00:19:08,043
伯爵,现在请在这里签字
Now, Count, if you'd be kind enough to sign here.

313
00:19:08,043 --> 00:19:09,151
好的
With great pleasure.

314
00:19:26,867 --> 00:19:28,662
洛马克斯先生!先生!
Mr Lomax! Sir!

315
00:19:29,450 --> 00:19:31,657
简!   发生什么事了?   我不知道
Jane!   What's happening?   I don't know.

316
00:19:32,060 --> 00:19:33,407
几点了?
What time is it?

317
00:19:33,407 --> 00:19:35,165
请你们到楼下去
If you'd all like to gather downstairs...

318
00:19:38,339 --> 00:19:40,739
对不起,把你们都吵醒了
I'm sorry to have to wake you all up

319
00:19:40,739 --> 00:19:45,240
但是洛马克斯先生的一位警卫被打昏了
but one of Mr Lomax's security staff was found unconscious.

320
00:19:45,240 --> 00:19:46,125
是不是?
Is that so?

321
00:19:46,125 --> 00:19:47,741
是的,先生.是罗伯茨
That's right, sir. Roberts.

322
00:19:47,741 --> 00:19:50,763
埃弗斯利,我们都在这里了吗?   是的
All present and correct, Eversleigh?   Indeed so.

323
00:19:50,763 --> 00:19:52,614
我想还少一位呢
I believe we're one short.

324
00:19:52,614 --> 00:19:54,556
伯爵   除了伯爵
The Count.   Out for the count.

325
00:19:54,556 --> 00:19:57,406
我倒不奇怪,想想他喝成什么样了
That's no surprise, considering how he was knocking it back.

326
00:19:57,406 --> 00:19:59,000
看看能不能叫醒他
See if you can raise him.

327
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:00,419
他不在屋里,先生
He's not in his room, sir.

328
00:20:00,995 --> 00:20:02,287
什么?   他在哪?
What?   Where is he?

329
00:20:02,450 --> 00:20:04,566
我想我们应该搜一搜
Perhaps we need a search party.

330
00:20:04,566 --> 00:20:07,907
没错,杰夫斯,你和罗伯茨把后门封锁上
Indeed. Jaffers you and Roberts seal off the back door.

331
00:20:07,907 --> 00:20:09,536
班铎,你去看看以前仆人的住处
Bundle, the old servants' quarters.

332
00:20:09,536 --> 00:20:12,498
埃弗斯利,你和贝金索普小姐在一楼找
Eversleigh You and Miss Blenkinsopp, the ground floor,

333
00:20:12,498 --> 00:20:14,034
我和弗吉尼亚在楼上找
and Virginia and I will look upstairs.

334
00:20:14,034 --> 00:20:15,346
弗吉尼亚怎么不能和我一起找?
Why Can't Virginia come with me?

335
00:20:15,346 --> 00:20:16,656
没时间了
We don't have time for this.

336
00:20:16,656 --> 00:20:18,701
你干嘛总想坏我的事?
Why do you always undermine me?

337
00:20:18,701 --> 00:20:20,768
你们俩消停一会行不?
Will you two kindly desist?

338
00:20:21,301 --> 00:20:22,446
谢谢了
Thank you.

339
00:20:22,446 --> 00:20:26,762
弗吉尼亚,你能不能上楼把他的药拿下来?
Now, Virginia, can you run upstairs and collect his medicine?

340
00:20:26,762 --> 00:20:29,823
简在这里看着他   好的
Jane will remain here and keep an eye on him.   Of course.

341
00:20:29,823 --> 00:20:33,227
其他人我们分头找.好吗?
The rest of us can just as well look by ourselves. Agreed?

342
00:20:37,978 --> 00:20:40,879
路德维格伯爵
Count Ludwig.

343
00:20:41,124 --> 00:20:42,504
路德维格伯爵
Count Ludwig.

344
00:20:44,767 --> 00:20:47,749
这样不好吧
I wouldn't think that's wise.

345
00:20:47,749 --> 00:20:49,295
大概不好
Probably not.

346
00:20:49,733 --> 00:20:51,303
你来点?
What about you?

347
00:20:51,559 --> 00:20:53,221
好啊
Why not.

348
00:20:59,890 --> 00:21:03,375
我们都多久没说过话了啊,你和我?
Seems ages since we talked, you and I?

349
00:21:04,712 --> 00:21:08,292
玛德琳这些年来也没怎么跟你联络了
Had been Madeleine rather lost touch with you over the years.

350
00:21:08,584 --> 00:21:10,577
不在一起难免会渐渐疏远吧
One grows apart, I think.

351
00:21:10,577 --> 00:21:11,898
大概是的
I suppose.

352
00:21:11,898 --> 00:21:16,147
不过,我真的很感激你一直为我留心弗吉尼亚的事
Still, I'm so grateful that you keep an eye on Virginia for me.

353
00:21:16,698 --> 00:21:18,825
当爸爸的也有做不到的事啊
A father can only do so much.

354
00:21:21,139 --> 00:21:24,288
这几年来,自从玛德琳...
And these past years, since Madeleine...

355
00:21:25,281 --> 00:21:28,462
反正过的不容易啊
Well, it's not been easy.

356
00:21:28,749 --> 00:21:31,344
我听说你想搬去伦敦住
I gather you're hoping to move to London.

357
00:21:31,973 --> 00:21:34,266
班铎可不允许
Not if Bundle can help it.

358
00:21:36,415 --> 00:21:40,986
哦,可怜的孩子,这里是她唯一的家
Oh, poor child, it's the only home she's ever known, you see

359
00:21:41,459 --> 00:21:45,789
但实际上记忆根本不是什么安慰
The truth is memories are no consolation.

360
00:21:46,734 --> 00:21:49,031
那些好的也不是
Not even the good ones.

361
00:21:49,722 --> 00:21:50,790
我把你的药拿来了
I've brought your medicine.

362
00:21:51,836 --> 00:21:55,195
谢天谢地我还有一双女儿啊
Thank God for my darling girls.

363
00:21:55,195 --> 00:21:56,543
爸爸
Daddy.

364
00:22:01,939 --> 00:22:03,510
乔治?   等会的!
George?   Not now!

365
00:22:03,510 --> 00:22:06,593
那声音好像是...   是开枪吗?
That sounded almost like...   Was that a gunshot?

366
00:22:07,594 --> 00:22:09,188
关上那扇门!
Someone close that door!

367
00:22:15,505 --> 00:22:17,970
你们找到他了吗?
Well, where is he? Any sign?

368
00:22:17,970 --> 00:22:20,750
你听到了吗?   大概半个郡都听到了
Did you hear it?   I think half the county heard it.

369
00:22:20,750 --> 00:22:21,994
他不会凭空消失啊
He can't have just vanished. 

370
00:22:21,994 --> 00:22:24,596
没有什么小门,小屋子什么的?
Are there no doorways, no outbuildings?

371
00:22:25,703 --> 00:22:28,043
你想不会是...   我们的秘门
You don't think...?   Our little door.

372
00:22:38,304 --> 00:22:40,424
啊!   拿着
Ah!   Take that.

373
00:22:41,507 --> 00:22:43,917
墙上应该有电筒,在这呢
Should be torches on the wall. Here is it. 

374
00:22:43,917 --> 00:22:45,188
自己拿一个   走啊,简
Help yourself.   Come on, Jane.

375
00:22:59,905 --> 00:23:02,423
这是血吗?   看起来像
What is that? Blood?   Looks like it.

376
00:23:13,159 --> 00:23:14,432
安东尼?
Anthony?

377
00:23:14,989 --> 00:23:16,709
我想他是中枪了   什么?
I think he's been shot.   What?

378
00:23:16,709 --> 00:23:21,121
奇...奇...奇...
Want! Want! Want!

379
00:23:23,010 --> 00:23:25,479
路德维格伯爵?能听到我说话吗?
Count Ludwig? Can you hear me?

380
00:23:25,479 --> 00:23:26,906
他还有气吗?   摸摸他的脉搏
Is he breathing?   Check his pulse.

381
00:23:26,906 --> 00:23:28,158
你能听到我吗?
Can you hear me?

382
00:23:28,808 --> 00:23:29,525
哦,天啊
Oh, God.

383
00:23:29,525 --> 00:23:31,737
不是我干的   我摸不到脉搏
It wasn't me.   I can't find a pulse.

384
00:23:33,277 --> 00:23:34,505
我想他是死了
I think he's dead.

385
00:23:35,001 --> 00:23:36,303
不是我干的!
It wasn't me!

386
00:23:46,726 --> 00:23:53,175
弗吉尼亚! 弗吉尼亚! 弗吉尼亚! 弗吉尼亚!
Virginia! Virginia! Virginia! Virginia!

387
00:23:53,285 --> 00:23:55,213
他是个多可爱的人啊
He was such an enchanting man.

388
00:23:56,659 --> 00:23:58,137
还是我们的客人
And he was our guest.

389
00:23:59,965 --> 00:24:02,833
我相信事情不是我们想的那样的
I'm sure there's a perfectly innocent explanation.

390
00:24:05,533 --> 00:24:06,859
弗吉尼亚!
Virginia!

391
00:24:07,397 --> 00:24:09,627
我得去找他   你敢!
I should go to him.   Don't you dare.

392
00:24:09,677 --> 00:24:11,880
别,回来!
Don't, come back.

393
00:24:13,234 --> 00:24:14,997
弗吉尼亚!   安东尼
Virginia!   Anthony.

394
00:24:15,671 --> 00:24:17,519
我的爱人   安东尼!
My love.   Anthony!

395
00:24:17,519 --> 00:24:19,717
你不能进去,小姐   我能跟他说话吗?
You can't go in, miss.   May I at least speak to him?

396
00:24:19,717 --> 00:24:23,029
恐怕不行啊   哦求你了,求你了
I'm sorry, miss.   Oh, please. Please.

397
00:24:26,196 --> 00:24:29,218
安东尼你为什么会出现在这里?
Anthony, what are you even doing here?

398
00:24:29,218 --> 00:24:33,423
弗吉尼亚...你得答应我一件事
Virginia... You must promise me something.

399
00:24:34,110 --> 00:24:35,097
什么事都行
Anything.

400
00:24:35,097 --> 00:24:38,092
求你...答应我你会忘记我
Please...promise me you'll forget me.

401
00:24:40,157 --> 00:24:43,597
安东尼?你吓着我了
Anthony? You're scaring me.

402
00:24:44,305 --> 00:24:45,950
安东尼
Anthony.

403
00:24:53,489 --> 00:24:54,327
芬驰
Finch.

404
00:24:55,060 --> 00:24:58,266
见到你太好了
Thank God. Good to see you again.

405
00:24:58,266 --> 00:25:02,105
芬驰探长,苏格兰场的领袖
Inspector Finch. The guru of Scotland Yard.

406
00:25:02,105 --> 00:25:06,211
芬驰?他长得像只猫,你不觉得吗?
Finch? He looks quite like a cat, don't you think?

407
00:25:07,685 --> 00:25:10,245
我讨厌猫   嘘!
I loathe cats.   Ssh!

408
00:25:14,635 --> 00:25:18,417
我猜他在内政部一定有不少粉丝吧
I gather he has devotees all over the Home Office.

409
00:25:18,417 --> 00:25:20,739
大家都觉得他很神秘呢
They regard him as some sort of mystic.

410
00:25:20,739 --> 00:25:24,317
有点像诺里奇的朱利安,不过是拥有逮捕权的
A bit like Julian of Norwich, only with powers of arrest.

411
00:25:24,317 --> 00:25:25,923
我们对受害人都有什么了解?
What do we know of the victim?

412
00:25:26,107 --> 00:25:28,351
1892年生于维也纳
Born Vienna, 1892.

413
00:25:28,351 --> 00:25:31,421
父母有钱,年轻的时候常到处周游
Wealthy parents. Travelled about a good deal in his youth.

414
00:25:31,421 --> 00:25:33,362
就是喜欢到处玩的那种人
Something of a wandering spirit.

415
00:25:33,362 --> 00:25:35,289
战后很快进入了政界
Entered politics soon after the war.

416
00:25:35,289 --> 00:25:38,132
我让我的人在镇上找个地方给你住
I can get my chap to find you a place in the town.

417
00:25:38,132 --> 00:25:39,592
没必要,我就住在烟囱大厦
No need. I shall be staying at Chimneys. 

418
00:25:39,592 --> 00:25:41,255
谋杀犯可不打点上班
Murder rarely keeps office hours.

419
00:25:41,255 --> 00:25:41,933
你好
Hello.

420
00:25:44,297 --> 00:25:45,397
呼吸一下新鲜空气
Bit of fresh air.

421
00:25:47,863 --> 00:25:51,099
如果处理的不好,会成为政治上的灾难
Politically this could be a disaster, if not handled with care.

422
00:25:51,099 --> 00:25:52,015
是啊
Indeed.

423
00:25:52,598 --> 00:25:55,337
就是说女士们都早早休息了?
So the ladies retired early?

424
00:25:55,337 --> 00:25:56,989
我们要谈生意
We had some business.

425
00:25:57,830 --> 00:26:01,732
与此无关   他要买下烟囱大厦
Er...not relevant.   He wanted to buy Chimneys.

426
00:26:01,732 --> 00:26:03,312
他要买下烟囱大厦?
He wanted to buy Chimneys?

427
00:26:03,312 --> 00:26:07,493
他的建议是由政府买下这栋房子,再以礼物的形式赠予伯爵
Well, the proposal was that the government would purchase the house,

428
00:26:07,493 --> 00:26:10,832
他的建议是由政府买下这栋房子,再以礼物的形式赠予伯爵
and then pass it on to Count Ludwig as a gift.

429
00:26:10,832 --> 00:26:12,995
算是贿赂吗?   别瞎说...
A bribe?   Don't be absurd...

430
00:26:12,995 --> 00:26:14,257
是给他个人的贿赂
A personal bribe.

431
00:26:14,604 --> 00:26:19,027
作为回报,他会把他们的重工业分一杯羹给我们
In return for which, he hands over a share of their heavy industry.

432
00:26:20,347 --> 00:26:22,851
我们对此事的道德立场是什么?
Where do we stand on that, morally?

433
00:26:22,851 --> 00:26:24,265
我想反正是不会拒绝的
Well back, I'd have thought.

434
00:26:25,485 --> 00:26:28,435
有买卖的文件吗?
Is there paperwork for this sale?

435
00:26:28,435 --> 00:26:32,983
签好字,封好印,锁在我屋抽屉里呢
Signed, sealed and in my room on the top drawer.

436
00:26:33,561 --> 00:26:35,459
现在已经没用了
All academic now, of course.

437
00:26:35,459 --> 00:26:36,940
了解
Understood.

438
00:26:37,675 --> 00:26:41,145
凯特勒姆勋爵,一扇门关上了,另一扇打开了
As one door closes, another stands ajar, Lord Caterham.

439
00:26:42,669 --> 00:26:44,060
确实
Indeed.

440
00:26:45,801 --> 00:26:47,865
各位先生们是什么时候休息的?
So you gentlemen retired at...

441
00:26:47,865 --> 00:26:50,062
差一刻十一点的时候
About a quarter to eleven.

442
00:26:50,062 --> 00:26:51,755
直到我们被铃声惊醒
Until we were woken by the fire bell.

443
00:26:51,755 --> 00:26:53,508
洛马克斯先生!先生!
Mr Lomax! Sir!

444
00:26:53,508 --> 00:26:57,141
什么时候?   差二十分到午夜
At what time?   Twenty to midnight.

445
00:26:57,141 --> 00:26:58,991
我们都到了楼下
We all met downstairs.

446
00:26:58,991 --> 00:27:02,299
没见到伯爵,所以我们就去找他
No sign of the Count. So off we went, looking for him.

447
00:27:02,299 --> 00:27:05,323
除了克莱门特和我
All save Clement and myself.

448
00:27:05,323 --> 00:27:06,889
然后就砰地一声
Next thing... Boom!

449
00:27:08,122 --> 00:27:09,276
枪声吗?
The gunshot?

450
00:27:09,550 --> 00:27:13,058
他一直都在通道里,就几码之外
He was in the passageway all along. Just a few yards away.

451
00:27:13,887 --> 00:27:15,647
武器上有指纹吗?
Any fingerprints on the weapon?

452
00:27:16,348 --> 00:27:18,169
没有
Regrettably not.

453
00:27:18,169 --> 00:27:21,946
但是我们抓到了犯人,安东尼凯德
Still, we have the culprit. Anthony Cade.

454
00:27:21,946 --> 00:27:24,851
当然了,要问他几句话
He has one or two questions to answer, certainly.

455
00:27:25,260 --> 00:27:27,963
我能看看尸体吗?   我带你去   谢谢
May I see the body?   I shall take you there at once.   Thank you.

456
00:27:27,963 --> 00:27:29,519
哦,还是让...
Or perhaps Miss...

457
00:27:30,835 --> 00:27:33,749
马普尔   马普尔小姐,方便吗?
Marple.   Marple. Yes. If it's no inconvenience?

458
00:27:34,263 --> 00:27:37,492
哦,行啊,没问题
Oh. Well, no, not at all.

459
00:27:47,485 --> 00:27:52,101
都过了就寝时间近一个小时了,他在这里干嘛?
What was he doing here, almost an hour after he went to bed?

460
00:27:53,725 --> 00:27:59,161
晚餐时他说对凡代克的画很感兴趣
He showed an interest over dinner in the Van Dyck portrait.

461
00:27:59,161 --> 00:28:03,392
或许是回来...   自己欣赏一会?
I suppose the Count could have returned...    A private viewing? 

462
00:28:03,422 --> 00:28:04,801
可能是吧
I suppose.

463
00:28:04,859 --> 00:28:07,252
碰巧秘门开了
And chanced upon the secret door.

464
00:28:07,721 --> 00:28:13,114
不过这世上没什么巧合不是吗?
Except that nothing quite happens by chance, does it? Not really.

465
00:28:14,655 --> 00:28:16,982
或者这只是我的偏见?
Or is that my tidy-minded preference?

466
00:28:25,770 --> 00:28:28,205
我注意到你身边没有人
I see you don't have a man with you.

467
00:28:31,937 --> 00:28:32,953
什么?
I'm sorry?

468
00:28:33,735 --> 00:28:37,898
嗯,一般探长都会带个人
Well, inspectors nowadays tend to have a man with them.

469
00:28:37,941 --> 00:28:42,051
啊   或许你喜欢自己独行?
Ah.   Perhaps you prefer to muse alone?

470
00:28:42,051 --> 00:28:46,691
或许没人愿意跟我做搭档   哦
Perhaps no man would have me.   Oh.

471
00:28:46,691 --> 00:28:51,649
这些血...   他就在这里被射伤
This blood...   He was shot here.

472
00:28:52,265 --> 00:28:57,579
也可能是从这边一路爬或者走或者被拖过来的
And crawled, staggered, or was dragged this-a-way...

473
00:28:57,579 --> 00:29:03,206
在这里被发现时倒在凯德先生的怀里
..where he was found in the arms of Mr Cade. Here.

474
00:29:03,206 --> 00:29:06,157
然后在这里倒向可怜的弗吉尼亚
Before falling on poor Virginia. Here.

475
00:29:07,782 --> 00:29:10,989
显然是这样的
All fairly straightforward, apparently.

476
00:29:17,824 --> 00:29:19,252
啊哈
Ah-ha.

477
00:29:26,361 --> 00:29:27,672
是封信吗?
Is it a letter?

478
00:29:29,277 --> 00:29:31,301
不是
Not quite.

479
00:29:34,341 --> 00:29:37,562
高音谱号   还是位艺术鉴赏家呢
A treble clef.    A virtuoso.

480
00:29:37,893 --> 00:29:40,763
您能拿着这个帮我研究研究吗,马普尔小姐
Perhaps you could take this and study it for me, Miss Marple.

481
00:29:42,359 --> 00:29:43,313
好的
Very well.

482
00:29:50,730 --> 00:29:53,117
伯爵死前说了些什么
The Count said something before he died.

483
00:29:53,117 --> 00:29:57,367
奇,奇...   奇?你确定吗?
Want, want...   Want? Are you sure?

484
00:29:57,367 --> 00:29:59,578
嗯   什么意思呢?
Mm-hm.    Meaning?

485
00:29:59,858 --> 00:30:03,683
或许是想说什么话,临死之言
Well, I suppose we all want something, even at death's door.

486
00:30:04,361 --> 00:30:05,591
遗言之类的
Kiss of life, perhaps?

487
00:30:06,475 --> 00:30:09,621
你怎么到这里的?   我从那边翻墙进来
How did you get here?   I climbed over the wall.

488
00:30:09,621 --> 00:30:11,063
我要进房子里
I was eager to get up to the house

489
00:30:11,063 --> 00:30:13,406
这位先生挡住了我的路
and this gentleman was blocking the path.

490
00:30:13,406 --> 00:30:14,741
能站一下位置吗,先生?
Would you mind, sir?

491
00:30:20,867 --> 00:30:22,257
我记得
Well, as I remember,

492
00:30:25,101 --> 00:30:26,584
我从这边过来
I came from around here.

493
00:30:29,793 --> 00:30:32,743
我看到了他,我慌神了
Then I spotted the gentleman, I panicked,

494
00:30:32,743 --> 00:30:34,869
然后...   你袭击了他
and then...   You hit him.

495
00:30:37,702 --> 00:30:40,386
是的,真抱歉
Yes, I am sorry about that.

496
00:30:40,386 --> 00:30:41,917
用这个吗?
Using this?

497
00:30:42,794 --> 00:30:43,769
是的
Exactly.

498
00:30:46,914 --> 00:30:49,947
是什么时间?   11点33分整
What time was that?   11:33. Precisely.

499
00:30:50,607 --> 00:30:52,191
我记得这么清楚是因为我看表了
I remember because I looked at my wrist watch.

500
00:30:52,191 --> 00:30:54,685
你眼力真好啊,凯德先生
I envy your eyesight, Mr Cade.

501
00:30:54,685 --> 00:30:56,192
是这样的
You see, that's the thing.

502
00:30:56,972 --> 00:31:00,742
我看到表是因为楼上有间房间的灯亮了
I know, because there was a light on in one of the upstairs rooms.

503
00:31:03,320 --> 00:31:06,291
二楼,右数第二间
It was first storey and then second to the right.

504
00:31:06,291 --> 00:31:10,458
我记得有人生火了
Now, I can remember because someone had lit a fire.

505
00:31:10,458 --> 00:31:12,335
这么暖和的天还生火吗
Rather a warm night for a fire.

506
00:31:12,335 --> 00:31:16,147
上面的烟囱里有烟冒出来
Well, there was definitely smoke coming out of the chimney above.

507
00:31:17,981 --> 00:31:20,998
反正,这个时候我已经很慌乱了
Anyway, at this stage common sense sounded the retreat.

508
00:31:20,998 --> 00:31:21,830
你听到铃声了吗?
Did you heed the warning?

509
00:31:21,830 --> 00:31:24,281
没有,就像我说的,我慌神了
Well, sadly, common sense and I are no longer on speaking terms

510
00:31:24,281 --> 00:31:27,845
