00:40:16,715 --> 00:40:20,334
所以看上去是右数第二间,实际上...
So that what appears to be second from the right is, in fact...

680
00:40:20,334 --> 00:40:21,562
是第三间
Third from the right.

681
00:40:22,183 --> 00:40:26,509
那么快要枪响的时候是谁起来了呢?
So who was up and about moments before the gunshot?

682
00:40:28,910 --> 00:40:33,206
柴德维尔,能谈谈吗?
Miss Treadwell, might I have a word please?

683
00:40:37,371 --> 00:40:40,611
11点33分的时候你的卧室灯是亮的
At 33 minutes past 11 your bedroom light was on,

684
00:40:40,611 --> 00:40:42,385
距枪响只有12分钟
12 minutes before the gunshot.

685
00:40:42,385 --> 00:40:44,169
是,就那么一会
Yes. Briefly.

686
00:40:44,169 --> 00:40:45,420
能说说是为什么吗?
Can you tell me why?

687
00:40:46,989 --> 00:40:49,262
我想跟路德维格伯爵说话
I wished to speak to Count Ludwig,

688
00:40:49,766 --> 00:40:53,477
不过他床上没人,我就回屋了
but noticing his bed was unoccupied, I returned to my room.

689
00:40:53,477 --> 00:40:56,046
你为什么想跟他说话呢?
Any particular reason for wishing to speak to him?

690
00:40:56,723 --> 00:40:58,156
哦,他...
Oh, he'd...

691
00:40:59,491 --> 00:41:02,335
他早些时候说过想加条毯子
earlier in the evening he'd asked for an extra blanket.

692
00:41:02,335 --> 00:41:04,989
你生火了吗?
So perhaps you lit a fire?

693
00:41:05,574 --> 00:41:08,539
什么?   还是11点33的时候
I beg your pardon?    At the same time. 11:33.

694
00:41:09,963 --> 00:41:12,136
没有,昨晚没生火
No fires last night. I...

695
00:41:12,405 --> 00:41:14,117
要是有人生火了我会知道的
I would have known, you see.

696
00:41:16,420 --> 00:41:21,670
你知道,昨天我有种奇怪的感觉你好像认识他
You know, it's funny, but yesterday I really felt that you knew him.

697
00:41:25,461 --> 00:41:27,778
看起来是个大场面啊
This looks a very grand affair.

698
00:41:27,778 --> 00:41:29,513
他们那个时候是很气派的
That's how they did it in those days.

699
00:41:29,513 --> 00:41:32,296
这后面的是乐队吗?
And this would be the orchestra, at the back here?

700
00:41:34,218 --> 00:41:35,928
他们那天演奏的是什么?
What sort of music did they play?

701
00:41:36,606 --> 00:41:37,959
华尔兹,大部分是
Waltzes, mainly.

702
00:41:37,959 --> 00:41:39,838
维也纳华尔兹吗?
Viennese waltzes?

703
00:41:42,372 --> 00:41:45,736
这是他,是不是?那里,路德维格伯爵
It's him, isn't it? There. Count Ludwig.

704
00:41:45,821 --> 00:41:48,151
这么说他以前来过
So he has been here before.

705
00:41:48,680 --> 00:41:51,270
还是在乐队里呢
And where else but in the orchestra?

706
00:41:53,880 --> 00:41:58,148
这么多年后为什么又回来呢?
What brought you back after all these years?

707
00:42:01,571 --> 00:42:03,263
柴德维尔小姐,你知道吗?
Any thoughts, Miss Treadwell?

708
00:42:05,983 --> 00:42:09,163
他是自作孽不可活   你说什么?
He got no more than he deserved.   I'm sorry?

709
00:42:13,332 --> 00:42:15,993
那个女孩...    失踪的女孩?
The girl who...   Who disappeared?

710
00:42:15,993 --> 00:42:18,643
艾格尼丝   客厅女仆,是的
Agnes.   The parlour maid, yes.

711
00:42:18,643 --> 00:42:20,936
艾格尼丝出什么事了?
Whatever happened to Agnes?

712
00:42:21,885 --> 00:42:24,575
晚宴那晚,我...
That night after the party, I...

713
00:42:24,575 --> 00:42:26,266
我看到光...
I saw a light...

714
00:43:24,051 --> 00:43:26,312
我就是看到这座坟墓开了
This was the tomb I saw opened.

715
00:43:26,312 --> 00:43:29,115
她的尸体,就倒在这里
Her body, it was down there.

716
00:43:40,307 --> 00:43:41,495
我来帮你
Let me help you.

717
00:43:41,495 --> 00:43:42,940
克莱门特,你没问题吗?
Clement, are you sure?

718
00:44:14,089 --> 00:44:15,393
艾格尼丝
Agnes.

719
00:44:17,480 --> 00:44:18,631
她的围裙
Her apron.

720
00:44:20,268 --> 00:44:21,691
可怜的孩子
Poor child.

721
00:44:21,826 --> 00:44:27,237
这么长时间,我们一直说她是个贼呢
All this time, we said she was the thief.

722
00:44:37,826 --> 00:44:40,210
我想你应该告诉我们到底出了什么事
I think it's time you told us what happened.

723
00:44:41,351 --> 00:44:44,177
女主人,她有一次跟我说
The mistress, she confided in me once.

724
00:44:44,177 --> 00:44:46,281
玛德琳?   她说什么了?
Madeleine?    What did she tell you?

725
00:44:47,623 --> 00:44:50,724
她说艾格尼丝那晚跟他在一起
She said Agnes was with him that night.

726
00:44:50,724 --> 00:44:51,878
跟谁?
With whom?

727
00:44:52,529 --> 00:44:54,733
一个音乐家,一个拉小提琴的
A musician. A fiddle player.

728
00:44:54,733 --> 00:44:56,719
哦,伯爵吗?
Oh, the Count?

729
00:44:56,778 --> 00:45:00,918
这么多年,你什么都不说
All these years. Not a word.

730
00:45:01,467 --> 00:45:04,004
我想说的,先生.但是...
I wanted to, sir. But...

731
00:45:04,528 --> 00:45:07,903
我觉得我要是说了,您会联络警察
I thought if I spoke out, you would contact the police,

732
00:45:07,903 --> 00:45:09,436
就会变成一桩丑闻
and there would be more of a scandal.

733
00:45:09,968 --> 00:45:12,467
这件事已经结束了您的职业生涯
It had already ruined your career and 

734
00:45:12,467 --> 00:45:15,676
如果宝石被偷都让您蒙羞,那...
if a stolen jewel could cast such a shadow, and then

735
00:45:16,247 --> 00:45:18,379
那一条人命...
and then the theft of a life...

736
00:45:18,775 --> 00:45:20,328
对不起
I'm so sorry.

737
00:45:20,590 --> 00:45:24,231
我做了什么啊?真抱歉
Oh, what have I done? I'm so sorry.

738
00:45:26,434 --> 00:45:29,486
怎么样?    她有所隐瞒
Well?   She's certainly hiding something.

739
00:45:51,726 --> 00:45:53,223
该死
Damn.

740
00:45:59,699 --> 00:46:00,529
哦
Oh.

741
00:46:02,321 --> 00:46:04,037
我想找点...   什么?
Wondered if there was any...   What?

742
00:46:04,037 --> 00:46:05,186
纸板
Cardboard.

743
00:46:06,353 --> 00:46:08,703
我想找点...不好意思,你在干嘛?
Wondered if there was any... Sorry, what are you...?

744
00:46:08,703 --> 00:46:11,189
你要纸板干嘛?   我在做点东西呢
What do you want cardboard for?   I'm making something.

745
00:46:11,754 --> 00:46:13,975
我不知道哪有纸板,所以帮不了你
Yes, well, I can't see any, so if you wouldn't mind.

746
00:46:15,207 --> 00:46:16,990
你打的什么主意,贝金索普小姐?
What are you up to, Miss Blenkinsopp?

747
00:46:16,990 --> 00:46:22,599
只想在这该死的大房子里找点清净
Just looking for some privacy in this big, old nasty...house.

748
00:46:22,599 --> 00:46:23,945
别动
Hands off.

749
00:46:23,945 --> 00:46:26,295
抱歉,不打扰你了
Sorry. I'll leave you to it.

750
00:46:42,083 --> 00:46:44,673
这很容易
Oh, it's child's play.

751
00:46:44,673 --> 00:46:47,105
是用音乐写的数学题
It's um... It's musical mathematics.

752
00:46:47,105 --> 00:46:47,751
你看看
Don't you see? 

753
00:46:47,751 --> 00:46:51,522
只要把音符和字母对上
One simply transposes the music from notes into letters.

754
00:46:51,522 --> 00:46:53,284
这两个八度
So two octaves...

755
00:46:54,683 --> 00:46:58,508
是A到O,这11个升音
take us from A up to O, while these 11 sharps

756
00:46:58,508 --> 00:47:00,439
是直到Z
bring us all the way up to Z.

757
00:47:00,439 --> 00:47:03,977
密信就解开了.啦啦啦!
Your coded letter. La! La-la!

758
00:47:05,423 --> 00:47:08,159
拜托了,可别奉承我
Please, I cannot abide flattery.

759
00:47:08,159 --> 00:47:10,891
谢谢你,瑞佛小姐
Thank you, Lady Revel. Thank you.

760
00:47:11,385 --> 00:47:13,880
不客气   谢谢你,班铎
Very well.   Thank you, Bundle.

761
00:47:15,476 --> 00:47:18,678
因为这样,我挚爱的上尉...
"For this reason, my beloved Captain...

762
00:47:18,678 --> 00:47:20,531
我们不能再见面了
I can never see you again.

763
00:47:20,531 --> 00:47:24,976
请答应我,你有一天会回来取回最珍贵的珠宝
Promise me you will return one day for the greatest jewel.

764
00:47:24,976 --> 00:47:27,799
里士满二十,向北,三,向东
Richmond Twenty, North Three East."

765
00:47:27,799 --> 00:47:29,913
死人口袋里的情书
A love letter in the dead man's pocket.

766
00:47:29,913 --> 00:47:33,263
不完整,如果我们能多拿到几页,或有个日期就好了
Incomplete. If we had a couple more pages a date'd be helpful.

767
00:47:33,263 --> 00:47:36,760
不过手稿是用圆珠笔写的
Yes, though the manuscript was written in ballpoint pen.

768
00:47:36,760 --> 00:47:39,132
没错.那么说是这几年写的
Indeed. So, the last couple of years. Yes.

769
00:47:39,367 --> 00:47:41,387
是告别信吗?
Oh. A farewell?

770
00:47:42,375 --> 00:47:44,548
"挚爱的上尉",上尉?
"Beloved Captain." Captain?

771
00:47:44,548 --> 00:47:47,189
路德维格伯爵的假名
An alias for Count Ludwig,

772
00:47:47,189 --> 00:47:49,532
是为了让这段情事保密吧?
if this affair was to be kept quiet?

773
00:47:49,532 --> 00:47:52,258
伯爵的秘密情人,是艾格尼丝吗?
The Count had a secret lover. Agnes?

774
00:47:52,314 --> 00:47:53,655
大概是
Perhaps.

775
00:47:53,758 --> 00:47:55,699
但这怎么解释?
But what do we make of this?

776
00:47:55,699 --> 00:47:59,995
请答应我,你有一天会回来取回最珍贵的珠宝
"Promise me you will return one day for the greatest jewel."

777
00:47:59,995 --> 00:48:02,776
是不是...?   路德维格伯爵回到烟囱大厦
Is it possible...?   Count Ludwig came here to Chimneys

778
00:48:02,776 --> 00:48:05,093
不是为了铁矿,是为了更秘密的事情
not to discuss iron, but on a secret mission, 

779
00:48:05,093 --> 00:48:07,805
从信的内容来看,是为了取回被偷的迈索尔钻石
revealed within this letter, to recover the stolen Mysore Diamond

780
00:48:07,805 --> 00:48:10,241
而这钻石就在这栋房子里的某个地方
located somewhere in this house.

781
00:48:10,542 --> 00:48:11,935
怪不得要用密码写呢
No wonder it's in code.

782
00:48:13,087 --> 00:48:15,412
所以他是为了这个想买下烟囱大厦
That's why he wanted to buy Chimneys.

783
00:48:15,412 --> 00:48:18,687
“里士满二十,向北,三,向东”
"Richmond Twenty, North Three East."

784
00:48:18,687 --> 00:48:20,373
线索近在眼前啊
The evidence was before our eyes.

785
00:48:20,373 --> 00:48:22,337
凡代克的画?   他画的内容
The Van Dyck?   And the subject?

786
00:48:22,337 --> 00:48:24,297
里士满公爵
The Duke of Richmond.

787
00:48:29,551 --> 00:48:32,254
18,19,20
18, 19, 20.

788
00:48:36,063 --> 00:48:37,470
就在这吗?
So?

789
00:48:38,719 --> 00:48:39,534
就是这吧
So.

790
00:48:40,429 --> 00:48:42,809
被折磨我探长
Don't torment me, Inspector.

791
00:48:42,809 --> 00:48:46,146
你要是知道什么...    奇,奇...
If you're holding something back...   Want, want...

792
00:48:46,146 --> 00:48:47,378
他的遗言
His last words.

793
00:48:49,125 --> 00:48:50,255
除非...
Unless, of course...

794
00:48:50,255 --> 00:48:52,889
墙,墙
Vunt, vunt...

795
00:48:53,003 --> 00:48:56,823
除非他说的不是英语,而是他的母语
Unless of course he was speaking not English, but his mother tongue.

796
00:48:56,823 --> 00:48:59,179
不是"奇,奇",而是"墙,墙"
Not "want, want", but "vunt, vunt".

797
00:49:00,997 --> 00:49:02,983
是德语的"墙"
"Der Wand" in High German.

798
00:49:03,590 --> 00:49:05,610
或者是带有奥地利口音的"墙"
Or "vunt" in the Austrian dialect.

799
00:49:05,643 --> 00:49:06,723
什么意思呢?
Meaning?

800
00:49:06,723 --> 00:49:08,862
墙,墙
The wall, the wall.

801
00:49:08,862 --> 00:49:10,683
你觉得是...?
So, you think...? 

802
00:49:10,683 --> 00:49:15,311
你觉得钻石是藏在墙里什么地方吗?
You think the diamond is hidden somewhere in the wall?

803
00:49:19,026 --> 00:49:22,184
嗯,很好啊
Well. Bravo.

804
00:49:22,685 --> 00:49:24,378
不过,我觉得有个人能帮我们的忙
But, you know, I think I know a gentleman

805
00:49:24,378 --> 00:49:26,720
不过,我觉得有个人能帮我们的忙
who might shed a little more light on the matter.

806
00:49:26,720 --> 00:49:28,985
你当晚是陪你教母来的吗?
You were accompanying your godmother?

807
00:49:29,205 --> 00:49:31,245
叫...   索梅塞夫人
Lady...    Lady Somerset.

808
00:49:31,245 --> 00:49:34,830
没错.我们以前都叫她罗比
That's right. We all used to call her Robbie.

809
00:49:37,662 --> 00:49:39,140
一定很迷人
Must have been quite bewitching.

810
00:49:40,398 --> 00:49:42,408
什么?   钻石
What?   The diamond.

811
00:49:43,363 --> 00:49:45,197
哦,是的
Oh. I see.

812
00:49:45,197 --> 00:49:48,518
对于我来说就是有颜色的石头罢了,探长
Well, it's all just coloured glass to me, Inspector.

813
00:49:51,146 --> 00:49:52,863
你那里是什么?
What, what have you got there?

814
00:49:53,616 --> 00:49:56,024
32年的调查记录
Notes from the investigation in '32.

815
00:49:56,966 --> 00:49:59,702
也包括你的口供
Interviews with, among others, yourself.

816
00:49:59,702 --> 00:50:03,668
"我完全不记得钻石什么时候没有的"
"I have no recollection of said diamond's disappearance.

817
00:50:03,668 --> 00:50:05,430
"我当时在睡觉呢"
In fact, I was asleep."

818
00:50:05,430 --> 00:50:09,145
我从清晨就起来到处忙活了,说真的,探长
I'd been charging about since dawn. Really, Inspector...

819
00:50:09,145 --> 00:50:11,217
我注意到索梅塞夫人也很早就休息了
I see Lady Somerset retired early as well.

820
00:50:11,217 --> 00:50:15,085
我们跟偷窃毫无关系,我向你保证
We had nothing to do with any theft, I assure you.

821
00:50:17,111 --> 00:50:18,701
是这样的
The point is...

822
00:50:19,536 --> 00:50:21,152
你看
See for yourself.

823
00:50:23,001 --> 00:50:24,737
我那时年轻
I was a young rake.

824
00:50:26,395 --> 00:50:28,512
她又很容易上道
She was easily led.

825
00:50:30,152 --> 00:50:31,421
我懂了
I see.

826
00:50:31,978 --> 00:50:34,504
至少也知道个大概了
Well, at least, I have an inkling.

827
00:50:35,965 --> 00:50:38,545
他使用笔名写的吗
And he was writing under a nom de plume.

828
00:50:38,594 --> 00:50:41,908
路德维格伯爵有个假名?   嗯   上尉
Count Ludwig had an alias?    Mm-hm.   The Captain.

829
00:50:42,289 --> 00:50:43,070
奇怪
Odd.

830
00:50:43,070 --> 00:50:46,437
还有个秘密情人呢,信里面都写着呢
And a secret lover, to boot. It's all in the letter.

831
00:50:46,437 --> 00:50:48,936
谁是他的情人呢?
Who was she, the lover?

832
00:50:48,936 --> 00:50:51,559
我们猜是艾格尼丝   可怜的艾格尼丝
We wondered. Agnes?    Poor Agnes.

833
00:50:51,559 --> 00:50:53,698
不仅如此,伯爵好像跟钻石失窃还有关系
Not only that. The Count seems to have had a hand 

834
00:50:53,698 --> 00:50:55,536
不仅如此,伯爵好像跟钻石失窃还有关系
in the theft of the famous diamond.

835
00:50:55,536 --> 00:50:57,326
他把她甩了,是吗?
So he bumped her off, did he?

836
00:50:58,138 --> 00:51:00,460
两个贼分赃不均?
Two thieves fighting over the spoils?

837
00:51:00,460 --> 00:51:02,585
你们吃啊
Well, do start away, everyone.

838
00:51:02,585 --> 00:51:05,414
她不是唯一的一个,不是吗?
Yes, and she wasn't the only one, was she?

839
00:51:05,713 --> 00:51:07,723
唯一的受害者
The only victim, I mean.

840
00:51:07,723 --> 00:51:09,980
比尔,那个什么...
Bill, where is the...?

841
00:51:09,980 --> 00:51:11,399
就在这里,亲爱的
Right here, my dearest.

842
00:51:18,719 --> 00:51:22,401
烟囱大厦,缩放版的
Chimneys. Not quite to scale, I'm afraid.

843
00:51:22,517 --> 00:51:25,265
谋杀的那晚,我们都在楼下
The night of the murder. We all came downstairs.

844
00:51:25,265 --> 00:51:29,249
没错吧?我们找不到伯爵了,所以就分头找
Yes? And we couldn't find the Count, so off we all went.

845
00:51:29,838 --> 00:51:31,960
我们是分开的.是这样的
Separately. Now, this is the point.

846
00:51:31,960 --> 00:51:33,426
我们都聚在这里
This is where we all were.

847
00:51:33,426 --> 00:51:36,645
班铎,你在客房那边找
So, Bundle, you were upstairs in the guest wing.

848
00:51:37,216 --> 00:51:38,536
乔治也是
George was there also.

849
00:51:38,818 --> 00:51:40,378
柴德维尔在厨房
Treadwell, kitchen.

850
00:51:41,049 --> 00:51:43,327
贝金索普小姐,在外面的空地上
Miss Blenkinsopp, I believe, was on the terrace.

851
00:51:43,327 --> 00:51:44,512
比尔在书房
Bill study

852
00:51:44,512 --> 00:51:47,741
我先去了楼上,然后下楼到了会议室
and I was upstairs then down to the council chamber.

