Get off.

1190
01:12:59,920 --> 01:13:01,776
他连这个也做不好
He couldn't even get that right.

1191
01:13:02,729 --> 01:13:04,523
想证明什么呀?
What's he trying to prove?

1192
01:13:04,523 --> 01:13:06,710
至少证明了一件事
Well, he has proven one thing.

1193
01:13:07,308 --> 01:13:09,499
哦?   他的清白
Oh?   His innocence.

1194
01:13:11,764 --> 01:13:13,327
我能给你们演示一下吗?
May I show you?

1195
01:13:15,263 --> 01:13:16,291
抱歉
I'm so sorry.

1196
01:13:17,085 --> 01:13:18,936
你们准备好了就开始吧
Whenever you're ready.

1197
01:13:28,247 --> 01:13:29,921
大家都在位置上了吗?
Everybody in position?

1198
01:13:30,313 --> 01:13:32,200
在,在
Yes, yeah.

1199
01:13:32,200 --> 01:13:32,900
好了
Ready.

1200
01:13:32,900 --> 01:13:33,861
在
Yes.

1201
01:13:36,547 --> 01:13:38,479
好了警官,就等你了
Alright constable, when you're ready.

1202
01:13:46,394 --> 01:13:48,784
我们都站在那天晚上枪响的时候我们站的地方,是吗?
We were all standing just where we were 

1203
01:13:48,784 --> 01:13:51,252
我们都站在那天晚上枪响的时候我们站的地方,是吗?
the moment of the fatal gunshot. Agreed?

1204
01:13:51,252 --> 01:13:53,803
是的   情况是一模一样的吗?
Indeed.   Everything just as it was?

1205
01:13:54,480 --> 01:13:57,797
不,枪响,太轻了
No. The gunshot, it was too quiet.

1206
01:13:57,797 --> 01:14:00,930
是的,枪响轻多了,探长
Yes, it was much quieter, Inspector.

1207
01:14:01,535 --> 01:14:04,348
想凯德先生刚刚砸锤子的声音
Like Mr Cade's hammering a few moments ago,

1208
01:14:04,348 --> 01:14:08,594
我们以为是枪响的那一声震得我的耳朵都疼了
whereas the sound we thought was the gunshot made my ears ring.

1209
01:14:09,230 --> 01:14:12,407
凯德先生,你记得,在花园里
Mr Cade, you remember, out in the garden,

1210
01:14:12,407 --> 01:14:15,395
那天晚上很暖和,你看到了什么?
what did he see on that warm night?

1211
01:14:16,144 --> 01:14:17,983
有人生火了
Someone had lit a fire.

1212
01:14:18,439 --> 01:14:21,127
还有我们在垃圾箱里发现了一段电线
And then that off-cut of flex

1213
01:14:21,127 --> 01:14:23,396
完全不明白它为什么会出现在那里
that had no business being in the compost.

1214
01:14:23,396 --> 01:14:25,659
那是一段导火线,探长
A piece of fuse, Inspector.

1215
01:14:26,197 --> 01:14:30,130
杀害伯爵的人,那晚在烟囱里点了些东西
The Count's killer lit something in the chimney that evening.

1216
01:14:30,534 --> 01:14:35,099
利用导火线,设计好15分钟后会炸响
On a slow fuse, timed to explode 15 minutes later,

1217
01:14:35,099 --> 01:14:38,090
让我们以为我们听到的是枪响
to deceive us all that what we heard was a gunshot

1218
01:14:38,090 --> 01:14:40,850
但实际上听到的是爆竹炸响
when what we, in fact, heard was a firework.

1219
01:14:43,366 --> 01:14:45,651
探长,记得你说过的话吗?
What was it you said, Inspector?

1220
01:14:45,651 --> 01:14:49,344
"不管怎么样,凯德先生都是在通道里被发现的"
"Like it or not, Anthony Cade was found in that tunnel 

1221
01:14:49,344 --> 01:14:50,799
"身旁还有尚有余温的抢呢"
with the smoking gun."

1222
01:14:51,555 --> 01:14:54,804
但是如果那枪已经冷了呢?
But what if the gun was not smoking?

1223
01:14:54,804 --> 01:14:58,412
如果伯爵其实早就被射伤了
What if the Count was killed earlier than supposed,

1224
01:14:58,412 --> 01:15:02,130
在差一刻11点,男士们就寝之后
after the men retired from their business at quarter to eleven

1225
01:15:02,130 --> 01:15:05,877
但是在一个小时后铃响之前呢?
but before the alarm bell almost an hour later?

1226
01:15:06,317 --> 01:15:09,904
这么一来,凶手就可能是我们之中任何人了
Suddenly, the killer could be any one of us.

1227
01:15:09,904 --> 01:15:10,833
你确定吗?
Are you sure?

1228
01:15:10,833 --> 01:15:14,431
你记得伯爵在晚饭的时候,对里士满公爵画像表现出兴趣
You recall the Count's interest, over dinner,

1229
01:15:14,431 --> 01:15:16,433
你记得伯爵在晚饭的时候,对里士满公爵画像表现出兴趣
in The Duke Of Richmond?

1230
01:15:16,999 --> 01:15:20,588
要是在我们都休息之后,悄悄把伯爵请下来
No great feat to quietly invite the Count back 

1231
01:15:20,588 --> 01:15:22,361
要是在我们都休息之后,悄悄把伯爵请下来
after the rest of us were in bed,

1232
01:15:22,403 --> 01:15:26,964
请他看这个暗藏的机关,把它引到通道里,再打死他
show him the hidden bolt, tempt him inside, then shoot him,

1233
01:15:26,964 --> 01:15:31,160
把枪扔在他身边,我们发现的时候就像是凶手扔在那的
and toss the gun to be found later as if abandoned by the killer.

1234
01:15:32,551 --> 01:15:35,737
可惜伯爵没有马上死掉
Sadly for the Count, he didn't die straightaway.

1235
01:15:35,737 --> 01:15:38,767
这是凶手唯一的失误,如果他不是有意这么做的话
The murderer's only mistake, if mistake it was.

1236
01:15:38,767 --> 01:15:39,826
我的天!
Good God!

1237
01:15:39,944 --> 01:15:44,545
可怜的人,过了一会,当凯德先生发现他的时候他还活着呢
The poor man was still living when Mr Cade found him some time later.

1238
01:15:46,513 --> 01:15:47,898
继续说啊,简
Go on, Jane.

1239
01:15:48,864 --> 01:15:50,535
那些信件...
Those letters...

1240
01:15:51,339 --> 01:15:54,378
我真是很傻很天真
I've been woefully, unforgivably naive.

1241
01:15:54,934 --> 01:15:57,777
康斯坦斯和上尉,啊,多么浪漫啊
Constance and the Captain, ah, the romance of it.

1242
01:15:58,054 --> 01:16:00,643
让人看不出问题来了...
One gets swept along and yet...

1243
01:16:01,344 --> 01:16:03,029
我这么问吧
Let me pose a question.

1244
01:16:04,061 --> 01:16:07,467
一对情人,决心要隐瞒他们的罗曼史
A pair of lovers, determined to hide their secret,

1245
01:16:07,467 --> 01:16:10,003
他们当然要用假名通信了
might they not write under an alias?

1246
01:16:10,003 --> 01:16:12,396
所以路德维格伯爵自称上尉
Indeed, Count Ludwig called himself the Captain.

1247
01:16:12,396 --> 01:16:16,437
他是这样的,那么为什么只有伯爵用了假名呢?
So he did. But why just the Count and not Constance?

1248
01:16:16,437 --> 01:16:19,137
她不是和他一样害怕秘密被人发现吗?
Did she not fear exposure as much as him?

1249
01:16:20,160 --> 01:16:25,062
除非康斯坦斯也是个假名
Unless Constance was also an alias.

1250
01:16:25,259 --> 01:16:30,642
那么说信里的康斯坦斯不是柴德维尔了?
So the Constance of the letters was not Treadwell?

1251
01:16:31,900 --> 01:16:33,472
抱歉,班铎
Forgive me, Bundle.

1252
01:16:34,791 --> 01:16:38,118
我从你的剪贴簿里拿到了这个
I took this from your scrapbook.

1253
01:16:39,271 --> 01:16:41,142
一条狗,怎么了?
It's a dog. So what?

1254
01:16:41,142 --> 01:16:44,160
是妈妈养的第一条狗狗
Well, it's Mama's first mutt.

1255
01:16:44,160 --> 01:16:47,054
上尉,名字叫上尉
Captain. It was called Captain.

1256
01:16:47,054 --> 01:16:50,162
它特别喜欢柴德维尔,妈妈开他们的玩笑说...
It was so besotted with Treadwell Mama used to joke they were like...

1257
01:16:50,162 --> 01:16:51,283
他们是"完美的情人"
"Perfect lovers."

1258
01:16:54,433 --> 01:16:57,102
我们的妈妈想到的这些假名
Our mother must have thought of these aliases.

1259
01:16:57,102 --> 01:16:59,967
康斯坦斯和上尉,是我们的妈妈?
Constance and her Captain. Our mother?

1260
01:16:59,967 --> 01:17:01,972
她用"康斯坦斯"做假名
Took the alias "Constance".

1261
01:17:02,558 --> 01:17:05,417
你妈妈就是伯爵的秘密情人
Your mother was the Count's secret lover.

1262
01:17:12,470 --> 01:17:13,427
我不明白
I don't understand.

1263
01:17:13,427 --> 01:17:18,198
你是在说是伯爵和玛德琳偷了钻石吗?
Are you saying that the Count and Madeleine stole the diamond?

1264
01:17:18,198 --> 01:17:20,520
哦,那该死的钻石
Oh, that wretched diamond.

1265
01:17:20,520 --> 01:17:23,204
我们都太着迷于迈索尔钻石了
We're all so bewitched by the Mysore Diamond, 

1266
01:17:23,204 --> 01:17:26,429
我们提出自己的假设却忘记了事实
we forge our theories and forget the facts.

1267
01:17:26,429 --> 01:17:29,156
要看清事实的真相
It is so important to see things clearly,

1268
01:17:29,156 --> 01:17:32,343
像是透过一面玻璃而不是棱镜
as if through a pane of glass, and not a prism.

1269
01:17:32,343 --> 01:17:33,277
不好意思
Excuse me.

1270
01:17:36,094 --> 01:17:36,704
抱歉
Sorry.

1271
01:17:43,347 --> 01:17:44,514
我的天
Good God.

1272
01:17:54,463 --> 01:17:55,175
可以给我吗?
May I?

1273
01:17:55,175 --> 01:17:59,181
我想伯爵是不可能杀了艾格尼丝
I'm afraid there's no way the Count murdered Agnes 

1274
01:17:59,181 --> 01:18:01,044
然后带着钻石跑路的
and made off with the diamond.

1275
01:18:01,418 --> 01:18:04,451
因为钻石一直跟艾格尼丝在一起呢
Because the diamond has been with Agnes all the time.

1276
01:18:05,130 --> 01:18:08,692
就在坟墓里,是凶手留在那里的
In the tomb, just where the killer left it.

1277
01:18:11,246 --> 01:18:13,912
当我们找到可怜的艾格尼丝的遗骸的时候,记得吗?
When we found poor Agnes's bones, do you remember?

1278
01:18:16,449 --> 01:18:18,804
我们之中隐藏了一位演员
Your histrionics in the crypt.

1279
01:18:18,804 --> 01:18:20,326
是你拿走的,是不是?
You took it then, didn't you?

1280
01:18:21,170 --> 01:18:22,917
然后把它丢进池塘里
And dropped it in the fountain.

1281
01:18:24,518 --> 01:18:27,295
要不然你干嘛擦手呢?
Why else would you be drying your hands?

1282
01:18:37,295 --> 01:18:38,687
爸爸?
Daddy?

1283
01:18:40,003 --> 01:18:40,967
为什么?
Why?

1284
01:18:43,537 --> 01:18:46,344
32年宴会那晚
The night of the party, '32.

1285
01:18:47,287 --> 01:18:50,458
我弄丢了一个袖扣,你信吗
I'd lost a cufflink, if you can believe it.

1286
01:18:50,978 --> 01:18:53,665
我上楼去...
I went upstairs and then...

1287
01:19:00,060 --> 01:19:04,880
不,不.您不能往那边去,求您
No, no, no, no, you mustn't go in there, please.

1288
01:19:05,379 --> 01:19:07,372
求您听我的
Please, sir, listen to what I'm saying.

1289
01:19:08,873 --> 01:19:10,879
我不是有意杀她的
I'd not meant to kill her,

1290
01:19:11,201 --> 01:19:13,023
但她想要阻止我
but she tried to prevent me 

1291
01:19:13,023 --> 01:19:17,620
不想我看到我妻子和那个小提琴手在一起
from seeing my wife and the fiddle player.

1292
01:19:18,837 --> 01:19:21,804
然后我的大脑清晰了起来
And then my mind cleared.

1293
01:19:23,690 --> 01:19:25,310
我拿走了钻石
I took the diamond.

1294
01:19:26,265 --> 01:19:28,920
把它留在艾格尼丝身边
Left it with Agnes.

1295
01:19:28,920 --> 01:19:32,669
他们自然会以为是她拿着钻石跑掉了
Naturally it was assumed that she had run off with it.

1296
01:19:34,472 --> 01:19:39,654
那后就是跟我妻子撒一个善意的谎言
Then all that remained was to tell my wife a white lie.

1297
01:19:39,654 --> 01:19:42,186
告诉她有人看到艾格尼丝
You told her Agnes had been seen.

1298
01:19:42,186 --> 01:19:45,467
和维也纳的小提琴手在一起
Cavorting with the Viennese fiddler

1299
01:19:46,769 --> 01:19:50,137
而他还继续给她写信
who, of course, went on writing to her for quite some time,

1300
01:19:50,137 --> 01:19:51,959
但是我把那些信收起来了
but I took care of those letters.

1301
01:19:51,959 --> 01:19:53,918
那些信只会让她痛苦的
They would only have caused her pain.

1302
01:19:56,084 --> 01:19:58,167
知道吗,现在想想,真是好笑
You know, it's funny, looking back.

1303
01:19:59,212 --> 01:20:02,282
她那么容易就相信了
She was so easily deceived.

1304
01:20:03,478 --> 01:20:07,685
这些浪漫的东西是多么易碎
These romances are so fragile.

1305
01:20:08,573 --> 01:20:11,337
根本就没有真正的忠诚
There's no real devotion at all.

1306
01:20:11,746 --> 01:20:15,009
不像我们之间的感情那样
Not such as we all had,

1307
01:20:15,009 --> 01:20:21,532
在一起,作为一家人,在烟囱大厦
together, as a family, here at Chimneys.

1308
01:20:21,532 --> 01:20:23,194
她并不快乐
She was unhappy.

1309
01:20:23,897 --> 01:20:26,652
她被困在这里,怪不得会憋出病来
Trapped. No wonder she got ill.

1310
01:20:26,652 --> 01:20:30,394
但是她死后,你找到了那些以前的信件
But after she died, you found the earlier letters,

1311
01:20:30,394 --> 01:20:31,987
是不是,上尉写给她的那些
didn't you, from the Captain?

1312
01:20:32,370 --> 01:20:34,450
这么多年,她一直好好保管着
She'd kept them safe, all these years.

1313
01:20:34,450 --> 01:20:36,799
是啊
Yes, indeed.

1314
01:20:37,416 --> 01:20:39,400
每一句
Every word.

1315
01:20:39,791 --> 01:20:44,022
所以当洛马克斯先生给你看路德维格伯爵说
So that when Mr Lomax showed you the letter from Count Ludwig,

1316
01:20:44,022 --> 01:20:45,695
想要来访烟囱大厦的信的时候
suggesting a visit to Chimneys

1317
01:20:45,695 --> 01:20:47,669
你立刻认出了他的笔迹
you knew the handwriting at once.

1318
01:20:47,669 --> 01:20:51,424
跟那些信件上的字一模一样,你知道...
A precise match for the old love letters. And you knew...

1319
01:20:51,424 --> 01:20:55,890
上尉就要来了
The Captain was on his way.

1320
01:20:56,818 --> 01:20:58,491
但是整爆竹干嘛?
But why the firework?

1321
01:20:59,212 --> 01:21:01,526
干嘛非得11点45?
Why 11:45?

1322
01:21:01,844 --> 01:21:07,311
埃弗斯利先生,你写给凯德先生的那封信,是不是没封口?
Mr Eversleigh, is it possible that the letter you wrote to Mr Cade 

1323
01:21:07,311 --> 01:21:09,452
埃弗斯利先生,你写给凯德先生的那封信,是不是没封口?
was in fact left unsealed?

1324
01:21:10,738 --> 01:21:12,101
你的客人到了,先生
Your guest has arrived, sir.

1325
01:21:12,518 --> 01:21:14,112
还留在桌上?
Still on the desk?

1326
01:21:14,112 --> 01:21:16,421
爵爷桌上的信,请您用快递寄出去
Letters for posting on his Lordship's desk.

1327
01:21:20,812 --> 01:21:23,879
你只需要加上时间
All that remained was to add the time.

1328
01:21:28,293 --> 01:21:31,870
你自己给凯德写了并寄了那封信
You wrote and posted the letter to Cade yourself.

1329
01:21:32,479 --> 01:21:36,007
然后又设计枪响在11点45分,就是要陷害凯德
And staged the gunshot for 11:45 to incriminate Cade.

1330
01:21:36,574 --> 01:21:38,897
要除掉你的敌人最好的办法是什么?
What better way to be rid of your enemies?

1331
01:21:38,897 --> 01:21:41,343
杀一个嫁祸另一个
Frame one for the killing of the other.

1332
01:21:41,343 --> 01:21:45,441
凯德不是什么好人,你自己也承认了
Cade is no good. You said as much yourself.

1333
01:21:45,771 --> 01:21:48,929
至于他打算把你拐到非洲去...
And as for this plan to ship you off to Africa...

1334
01:21:48,929 --> 01:21:50,978
别这么看着我
Now, don't look at me like that. 

1335
01:21:50,978 --> 01:21:54,344
婚姻不能建立在谎言之上
You cannot build a marriage on lies.

1336
01:21:54,344 --> 01:21:56,451
不是应该建立在爱情之上吗?
Aren't you supposed to build it on love?

1337
01:21:57,904 --> 01:21:58,883
柴德维尔呢?
And Treadwell?

1338
01:21:59,656 --> 01:22:00,843
跟我们想的一样
As we thought.

1339
01:22:01,486 --> 01:22:07,981
不是毛地黄毒死的...而是你的补药
Poisoned not by the foxglove leaves...but by your tonic.

1340
01:22:09,292 --> 01:22:12,575
有效成分是洋地黄,过量摄入致死
Active ingredient: digitalis. A huge overdose.

1341
01:22:14,155 --> 01:22:16,233
我确实很后悔杀她
Now, I do regret that.

1342
01:22:16,233 --> 01:22:18,452
她是个忠诚的仆人
She was a faithful servant.

1343
01:22:18,452 --> 01:22:20,583
比你认为的更忠诚
More faithful than you knew.

1344
01:22:21,030 --> 01:22:24,051
你害怕她会把那段情事告诉探长
You were so fearful that she would tell the Inspector 

1345
01:22:24,051 --> 01:22:25,308
你害怕她会把那段情事告诉探长
about the affair. On the contrary.

1346
01:22:25,308 --> 01:22:26,463
恰恰相反
about the affair. On the contrary.

1347
01:22:26,463 --> 01:22:30,112
她却想尽办法保护她女主人的秘密
She was taking measures to protect her mistress's secret.

1348
01:22:30,503 --> 01:22:32,883
艾格尼丝的遗骸一被发现
As soon as Agnes's bones were recovered,

1349
01:22:32,883 --> 01:22:37,289
她就从你那里找到了信件放到自己屋里
she took the letters from amongst your possessions to her own room.

1350
01:22:38,035 --> 01:22:44,251
要是我不杀她,就不会有人知道了
If I'd let her live, no-one would have found out.

1351
01:22:44,251 --> 01:22:46,121
你是这个意思吗?
Is that what you mean?

1352
01:22:48,840 --> 01:22:51,759
好吧,那就是这样了
Well, that's it, then.

1353
01:22:51,986 --> 01:22:53,442
还有
Not quite.

1354
01:22:54,194 --> 01:22:54,940
爸爸?
Daddy?

1355
01:22:57,884 --> 01:23:00,527
"有一天会回来取回最珍贵的珠宝"
"Return one day for the greatest jewel."

1356
01:23:01,141 --> 01:23:02,672
别说了
You stop.

1357
01:23:02,672 --> 01:23:07,421
如果这珠宝是指的别的什么呢?
What if this jewel was a diamond of a different kind?

1358
01:23:07,421 --> 01:23:10,597
别说了!   不管是什么我们有权知道
Stop!   Whatever it is, we have a right to know.

1359
01:23:15,153 --> 01:23:16,495
玫瑰
A rose.

1360
01:23:16,495 --> 01:23:18,767
不是随便什么玫瑰
Not just any rose.

1361
01:23:20,033 --> 01:23:21,690
是里士满玫瑰
The Richmond rose.

1362
01:23:25,218 --> 01:23:27,453
"里士满二十,向北,三,向东"
"Richmond Twenty, North Three East."

1363
01:23:27,453 --> 01:23:29,789
里士满指的不是画像
The Richmond referred to is not the portrait.

1364
01:23:29,789 --> 01:23:33,172
没错,而是里士满玫瑰
Precisely. The rose of Richmond.

1365
01:23:33,172 --> 01:23:34,731
啊
Ah.

1366
01:23:36,157 --> 01:23:39,222
那么这些方向,是指向哪里的?
Well, these directions, where did they lead?

1367
01:23:42,309 --> 01:23:43,477
1,2...
One, two...

1368
01:23:58,723 --> 01:24:00,129
我不明白
I don't understand.

1369
01:24:00,887 --> 01:24:02,003
简?
Jane?

1370
01:24:02,549 --> 01:24:05,629
记得伯爵的遗言吗?
The Count's last words. Do you remember?

1371
01:24:05,629 --> 01:24:07,427
墙,墙
Der Wand. The wall.

1372
01:24:07,427 --> 01:24:10,446
我们以为他指的是通道里的墙
We thought he meant the wall in the passageway.

1373
01:24:10,446 --> 01:24:14,909
但是这美国藤,什么时候栽种的?
But this Virginia creeper, when was it planted?

1374
01:24:15,502 --> 01:24:22,074
玛德琳23年前栽下的,庆祝你的出生
Madeleine planted it 23 years ago to celebrate your birth.

1375
01:24:22,074 --> 01:24:24,011
美国藤(弗吉尼亚藤)
Virginia creeper.

1376
01:24:25,510 --> 01:24:29,432
我想他临死的时候一定想明白了
He knew, I'm sure he did, as he lay dying.

1377
01:24:29,754 --> 01:24:32,801
玫瑰,舞蹈...
The rose, the dance...

1378
01:24:33,693 --> 01:24:35,711
都变得明朗起来
..it all made sense.

1379
01:24:37,082 --> 01:24:40,248
我想那封密信是你妈妈临死的时候写给伯爵的
I think your mother wrote to the Count, 

1380
01:24:40,248 --> 01:24:42,183
我想那封密信是你妈妈临死的时候写给伯爵的
shortly before she passed away.

1381
01:24:43,423 --> 01:24:44,804
那封密信
The coded letter?

1382
01:24:47,217 --> 01:24:50,472
她不想让秘密跟她一起埋入地下
She didn't want the truth to die with her, not quite.

1383
01:24:52,036 --> 01:24:55,314
你的意思是...   你就是"最珍贵的珠宝"
So, you mean...   You were the "greatest jewel".

1384
01:24:55,621 --> 01:24:57,723
他来带你走的
He'd come to take you away.

1385
01:24:58,029 --> 01:25:00,129
我的小姑娘
My own little girl.

1386
01:25:07,597 --> 01:25:09,590
我的女儿
My darling girl.

1387
01:25:12,536 --> 01:25:14,639
他是我生父?
He was my father?

1388
01:25:19,923 --> 01:25:22,581
不,不
No. No.

1389
01:25:48,047 --> 01:25:50,996
如果你现在想放手...   我不会的
I feel, if you were to let go now...   I won't.

1390
01:25:51,301 --> 01:25:55,861
我就会离开...   我不会的
I'd just float off and...   I won't.

1391
01:26:00,220 --> 01:26:03,021
来吧,该来的躲不掉
Come on. No use putting off the inevitable.

1392
01:26:03,021 --> 01:26:05,179
你来说还是我来说?
Are you going to tell her or shall I?

1393
01:26:05,179 --> 01:26:09,148
我想我来说比较好
Oh, I think it's best coming from me.

1394
01:26:12,469 --> 01:26:13,673
贝金索普!
Blenkinsopp!

1395
01:26:22,108 --> 01:26:23,143
哦,天啊
Oh, dear.

1396
01:26:23,371 --> 01:26:25,981
哦,天啊.班铎肯定不喜欢这样
Oh, dear. Bundle won't like that at all.

1397
01:26:27,111 --> 01:26:30,084
但是你们不是要把烟囱大厦卖掉吧?
But you're not selling Chimneys?

1398
01:26:30,084 --> 01:26:34,124
班铎不想在这里呆着了,我也不想
Well, Bundle couldn't bear to stay on, and I don't want to live here,

1399
01:26:34,124 --> 01:26:35,438
你觉得呢?
so what do you think?

1400
01:26:35,438 --> 01:26:37,220
把麻烦都丢给贝金索普
Pass the whole headache on to Blenkinsopp 

1401
01:26:37,220 --> 01:26:39,808
让她去打理吧.干嘛不呢?
and her tea and scones. Why not?

1402
01:26:40,031 --> 01:26:42,640
她不会有事吧,我是说班铎?
Will she be all right? Bundle, I mean.

1403
01:26:42,640 --> 01:26:45,661
她会把精力放在别的什么地方
Oh, she'll foist herself onto some undeserving cause.

1404
01:26:45,661 --> 01:26:47,697
她爸爸?   大概吧
Her father?    I suppose.

1405
01:26:47,697 --> 01:26:48,673
那你呢?
And you?

1406
01:26:51,067 --> 01:26:52,509
他们来了
Here they come.

1407
01:26:54,644 --> 01:26:56,060
幸福的婚姻
A happy marriage.

1408
01:26:56,734 --> 01:26:58,385
也不会很难吧,是不是?
It can't be that difficult, can it?

1409
01:26:58,385 --> 01:27:00,152
跟随自己的心愿
Go with your heart.

1410
01:27:00,152 --> 01:27:01,261
像妈妈那样?
Like mother?

1411
01:27:01,932 --> 01:27:05,129
我一直在想,她要是真那么爱伯爵
I keep thinking, if she loved her Count so much,

1412
01:27:05,129 --> 01:27:07,552
为什么她又那么轻易的就相信他会跑掉呢?
why was she so quick to believe he'd run off?

1413
01:27:08,280 --> 01:27:11,491
我想爱真的需要勇气吧
I suppose love is an act of courage.

1414
01:27:16,865 --> 01:27:18,124
是的
Yes.

1415
01:27:25,320 --> 01:27:27,915
马普尔小姐   再见了,探长
Miss Marple.   Goodbye, Inspector.

1416
01:27:27,915 --> 01:27:31,842
谢谢你,现在我知道我太在意自己的名声了
Thank you. I see now I've grown too fond of my own reputation.

1417
01:27:32,905 --> 01:27:36,512
我那么想找到那该死的钻石
I was so bewitched by the blasted diamond.

1418
01:27:36,837 --> 01:27:39,831
现在看看我,成了你又一个手下败将
And now look at me. The latest of your casualties.

1419
01:27:42,037 --> 01:27:44,048
你看怎么样?   哦
What do you think?   Oh.

1420
01:27:44,697 --> 01:27:47,331
国际刑警组织想让我带着它去南非
Interpol want me to take it to South Africa,

1421
01:27:47,331 --> 01:27:49,467
给比勒陀利亚的那个家伙下个套
entrap this villainous fellow from Pretoria.

1422
01:27:49,467 --> 01:27:52,583
你知道探长,我真是不在乎这个钻石
You know, Inspector, I don't care for it at all.

1423
01:27:55,791 --> 01:27:56,770
再见
Goodbye.


